Belief  with George Noory.

00:00:42.742 --> 00:00:44.277 align:middle line:84%
>> [Background Sounds] Well,
welcome to  Beyond Belief.

00:00:44.277 --> 00:00:46.546 align:middle line:84%
Look, we're laughing and
smiling now, but by the end

00:00:46.546 --> 00:00:50.183 align:middle line:84%
of this program I
guarantee you we won't be.

00:00:50.183 --> 00:00:52.319 align:middle line:84%
Probably one of the most
frightening things I've ever

00:00:52.319 --> 00:00:57.491 align:middle line:84%
dealt with on this program --
EMPs -- electromagnetic pulses.

00:00:57.491 --> 00:00:58.692 align:middle line:90%
What are they?

00:00:58.692 --> 00:01:01.561 align:middle line:84%
A detonation by a nuke,
high above our atmosphere;

00:01:01.561 --> 00:01:05.398 align:middle line:84%
a coronal mass ejection;
an X-flare from the sun

00:01:05.398 --> 00:01:08.068 align:middle line:84%
which literally wipes
out our grid

00:01:08.068 --> 00:01:09.903 align:middle line:90%
and everything else with it.

00:01:09.903 --> 00:01:12.439 align:middle line:84%
Our special guest
tonight, William Forstchen,

00:01:12.439 --> 00:01:16.209 align:middle line:84%
author of  One Second After,
a critically acclaimed book

00:01:16.209 --> 00:01:18.945 align:middle line:84%
that Congress should
be reading every day.

00:01:18.945 --> 00:01:20.147 align:middle line:90%
William, welcome [applause].

00:01:20.147 --> 00:01:24.618 align:middle line:90%
Good to have you with us.

00:01:24.618 --> 00:01:25.185 align:middle line:90%
>> Thanks a lot.

00:01:25.185 --> 00:01:27.354 align:middle line:90%
>> Have a seat.

00:01:27.354 --> 00:01:30.089 align:middle line:84%
You are pretty gutsy,
my friend, coming...

00:01:30.089 --> 00:01:31.357 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, really?

00:01:31.357 --> 00:01:33.226 align:middle line:84%
>> ...up with a book like
this and a subject matter

00:01:33.226 --> 00:01:38.431 align:middle line:84%
that so many people just
simply don't want to listen to.

00:01:38.431 --> 00:01:40.232 align:middle line:90%
It scares them to hear this.

00:01:40.232 --> 00:01:41.301 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:01:41.301 --> 00:01:43.369 align:middle line:84%
>> Explain, first of
all, for everybody;

00:01:43.369 --> 00:01:45.105 align:middle line:90%
EMP, what does that mean?

00:01:45.105 --> 00:01:48.642 align:middle line:84%
>> EMP, shorthand for
electromagnetic pulse.

00:01:48.642 --> 00:01:53.345 align:middle line:84%
It is a by-product of
detonating a nuclear weapon.

00:01:53.345 --> 00:01:57.750 align:middle line:84%
The perfect storm scenario
for enemies is to pop one

00:01:57.750 --> 00:02:02.422 align:middle line:84%
to three nukes approximately
250 miles above the atmosphere.

00:02:02.422 --> 00:02:06.493 align:middle line:84%
In that first microsecond
of detonation,

00:02:06.493 --> 00:02:08.295 align:middle line:90%
the gamma ray burst coming off

00:02:08.295 --> 00:02:11.298 align:middle line:84%
of the bomb hits the
upper atmosphere,

00:02:11.298 --> 00:02:14.834 align:middle line:84%
triggers an electrostatic
discharge that cascades

00:02:14.834 --> 00:02:16.870 align:middle line:90%
down to the earth's surface.

00:02:16.870 --> 00:02:18.605 align:middle line:90%
One second after, it could take

00:02:18.605 --> 00:02:21.241 align:middle line:84%
out the entire power grid
of the United States.

00:02:21.241 --> 00:02:22.075 align:middle line:90%
>> Just like that.

00:02:22.075 --> 00:02:23.143 align:middle line:90%
>> Like that.

00:02:23.143 --> 00:02:25.412 align:middle line:84%
And Congressional
testimony back in '04,

00:02:25.412 --> 00:02:29.015 align:middle line:84%
which I base my book upon,
one expert said it would be

00:02:29.015 --> 00:02:31.318 align:middle line:84%
like throwing America
back a hundred years.

00:02:31.318 --> 00:02:34.588 align:middle line:84%
I disagree because people a
hundred years ago knew how

00:02:34.588 --> 00:02:36.756 align:middle line:84%
to live with the technology
of a hundred years ago.

00:02:36.756 --> 00:02:37.891 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:02:37.891 --> 00:02:39.693 align:middle line:84%
>> This would throw us
back a thousand years,

00:02:39.693 --> 00:02:42.395 align:middle line:84%
and the estimated
fatality rate for America,

00:02:42.395 --> 00:02:45.131 align:middle line:90%
90% by the end of one year.

00:02:45.131 --> 00:02:46.499 align:middle line:90%
>> 90%.

00:02:46.499 --> 00:02:48.501 align:middle line:84%
>> 90% will perish
in the first year.

00:02:48.501 --> 00:02:52.305 align:middle line:84%
>> Not that the pulse and the
explosion would physically kill

00:02:52.305 --> 00:02:54.474 align:middle line:90%
people, it's afterward.

00:02:54.474 --> 00:02:56.443 align:middle line:84%
It's with the grid down
and everything else.

00:02:56.443 --> 00:02:58.645 align:middle line:84%
>> The only people that
would be directly affected

00:02:58.645 --> 00:03:02.048 align:middle line:84%
in the first couple of minutes,
and I think about this flying

00:03:02.048 --> 00:03:03.316 align:middle line:90%
out here to meet with you...

00:03:03.316 --> 00:03:04.417 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:03:04.417 --> 00:03:05.685 align:middle line:84%
>> ...is walking to that
plane, look at that,

00:03:05.685 --> 00:03:07.354 align:middle line:84%
what they call mal
glass cockpit...

00:03:07.354 --> 00:03:08.021 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:03:08.021 --> 00:03:09.089 align:middle line:90%
>> Remember Sully?

00:03:09.089 --> 00:03:10.223 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:03:10.223 --> 00:03:12.959 align:middle line:84%
>> He lost his -- but he
still had his hydraulics

00:03:12.959 --> 00:03:15.762 align:middle line:84%
and his computer so he was able
to put that plane down safely.

00:03:15.762 --> 00:03:16.730 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:03:16.730 --> 00:03:18.164 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, if you lose
all the controls

00:03:18.164 --> 00:03:20.800 align:middle line:84%
in a modern airplane you can
jam the stick all you want...

00:03:20.800 --> 00:03:21.902 align:middle line:84%
>> And you want --
every plane that's

00:03:21.902 --> 00:03:23.169 align:middle line:90%
in the air at that time...

00:03:23.169 --> 00:03:24.137 align:middle line:90%
>> Going to go straight down.

00:03:24.137 --> 00:03:25.105 align:middle line:90%
>> ...they all go down.

00:03:25.105 --> 00:03:28.074 align:middle line:84%
>> It will make 911
look like a...

00:03:28.074 --> 00:03:28.842 align:middle line:90%
>> Small.

00:03:28.842 --> 00:03:30.377 align:middle line:90%
>> ...small in comparison.

00:03:30.377 --> 00:03:33.613 align:middle line:84%
>> An X-flare from
the sun, a big one.

00:03:33.613 --> 00:03:36.249 align:middle line:84%
If the sun and the
earth are directly

00:03:36.249 --> 00:03:37.350 align:middle line:90%
in front of each other...

00:03:37.350 --> 00:03:38.184 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:03:38.184 --> 00:03:39.352 align:middle line:90%
>> ...so that path is perfect.

00:03:39.352 --> 00:03:40.186 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:03:40.186 --> 00:03:41.454 align:middle line:90%
>> That could do the same thing.

00:03:41.454 --> 00:03:43.256 align:middle line:84%
>> Absolutely, and it's
happening all the time, George.

00:03:43.256 --> 00:03:46.726 align:middle line:84%
You and I have chatted a couple
of times before on your show.

00:03:46.726 --> 00:03:48.094 align:middle line:90%
Remember about a year ago...

00:03:48.094 --> 00:03:48.862 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:03:48.862 --> 00:03:50.263 align:middle line:90%
>> ...the sun popped one.

00:03:50.263 --> 00:03:54.501 align:middle line:84%
Now the sun all of the time is
throwing out what's called CMEs.

00:03:54.501 --> 00:03:57.403 align:middle line:84%
That stands for coronal
mass ejection.

00:03:57.403 --> 00:04:00.140 align:middle line:84%
They're flaring out all
the time, but the earth is

00:04:00.140 --> 00:04:01.875 align:middle line:90%
like a tiny little marble...

00:04:01.875 --> 00:04:02.442 align:middle line:90%
>> It's -- yeah.

00:04:02.442 --> 00:04:03.243 align:middle line:90%
>> ...three...

00:04:03.243 --> 00:04:04.477 align:middle line:90%
>> ...it's a moving target.

00:04:04.477 --> 00:04:06.446 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah. But that --
approximately once every hundred

00:04:06.446 --> 00:04:11.551 align:middle line:84%
to 150 years one of those
CMEs slams straight into us,

00:04:11.551 --> 00:04:15.622 align:middle line:84%
disrupts the magnetosphere and
can create a global shutdown

00:04:15.622 --> 00:04:18.124 align:middle line:84%
of the entire electrical
grid of the world.

00:04:18.124 --> 00:04:21.661 align:middle line:84%
>> Did that not happen on this
planet once before during the

00:04:21.661 --> 00:04:23.296 align:middle line:90%
era of the telegraph?

00:04:23.296 --> 00:04:25.398 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, 1859.

00:04:25.398 --> 00:04:28.702 align:middle line:84%
And I would urge listeners
who might be doubting this

00:04:28.702 --> 00:04:30.470 align:middle line:84%
or the folks in the
audience thinking, boy,

00:04:30.470 --> 00:04:32.539 align:middle line:84%
George has an interesting
guest here,

00:04:32.539 --> 00:04:35.208 align:middle line:84%
look up the Carrington
Event when you get

00:04:35.208 --> 00:04:36.276 align:middle line:90%
on the computer later.

00:04:36.276 --> 00:04:39.312 align:middle line:84%
Carrington Event --
it happened in 1859.

00:04:39.312 --> 00:04:40.880 align:middle line:90%
It hit with such intensity,

00:04:40.880 --> 00:04:44.317 align:middle line:84%
telegraphy wires were
melting off of the poles...

00:04:44.317 --> 00:04:45.452 align:middle line:90%
>> Unbelievable.

00:04:45.452 --> 00:04:47.087 align:middle line:84%
>> ...the railroad ties
were catching on fire.

00:04:47.087 --> 00:04:50.223 align:middle line:84%
Now think of how overbuilt
that technology was...

00:04:50.223 --> 00:04:51.358 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:04:51.358 --> 00:04:53.126 align:middle line:84%
>> ...compared to the
microelectronics we're

00:04:53.126 --> 00:04:56.396 align:middle line:90%
so dependent upon today.

00:04:56.396 --> 00:04:57.364 align:middle line:84%
>> Let's talk about this,
William, in two facets:

00:04:57.364 --> 00:05:00.233 align:middle line:84%
one is the nuke;
the other's the sun.

00:05:00.233 --> 00:05:01.001 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:05:01.001 --> 00:05:03.336 align:middle line:90%
>> Both, as we just said,

00:05:03.336 --> 00:05:06.906 align:middle line:84%
incredible dangers
to us, to our planet.

00:05:06.906 --> 00:05:08.441 align:middle line:84%
We're concerned about
North Korea.

00:05:08.441 --> 00:05:09.542 align:middle line:90%
>> We should be.

00:05:09.542 --> 00:05:11.544 align:middle line:84%
>> We're concerned about
Iran getting nukes.

00:05:11.544 --> 00:05:12.579 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:05:12.579 --> 00:05:14.914 align:middle line:90%
>> We question the ability

00:05:14.914 --> 00:05:18.618 align:middle line:84%
to reach the continental
United States with missiles.

00:05:18.618 --> 00:05:20.153 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to
worry about that.

00:05:20.153 --> 00:05:25.325 align:middle line:84%
All you have to do is
put a nuke on a ship,

00:05:25.325 --> 00:05:28.962 align:middle line:84%
launch it above the
atmosphere, and detonate it,

00:05:28.962 --> 00:05:31.765 align:middle line:84%
and we create this
horrible scenario.

00:05:31.765 --> 00:05:33.600 align:middle line:84%
>> George, the analogy
I give there is

00:05:33.600 --> 00:05:35.135 align:middle line:90%
if I was coming home every day

00:05:35.135 --> 00:05:38.138 align:middle line:84%
and I'm hearing a neighbor
shouting how he's going

00:05:38.138 --> 00:05:41.507 align:middle line:84%
to get me, and I peek over the
fence and he's target practicing

00:05:41.507 --> 00:05:42.675 align:middle line:90%
on a picture of my face...

00:05:42.675 --> 00:05:43.676 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:43.676 --> 00:05:44.878 align:middle line:84%
>> ...I think I better
start running.

00:05:44.878 --> 00:05:46.012 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't think that's
funny if he's doing that.

00:05:46.012 --> 00:05:47.280 align:middle line:84%
>> No. Or he's going
to say that he's going

00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:49.215 align:middle line:84%
to bathe my child
in nuclear death.

00:05:49.215 --> 00:05:50.417 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:50.417 --> 00:05:52.685 align:middle line:84%
>> The Iranians for years,
out in the Caspian Sea,

00:05:52.685 --> 00:05:57.156 align:middle line:84%
had them launching missiles
straight up and detonating them

00:05:57.156 --> 00:05:59.426 align:middle line:84%
and then claiming, oh,
it was a failed test.

00:05:59.426 --> 00:06:02.595 align:middle line:84%
That fits the profile
of how to launch an EMP.

00:06:02.595 --> 00:06:05.632 align:middle line:90%
Get a cargo container ship.

00:06:05.632 --> 00:06:06.866 align:middle line:84%
Folks might recall
-- remember a couple

00:06:06.866 --> 00:06:08.902 align:middle line:84%
of years ago a cargo
container ship from Russia...

00:06:08.902 --> 00:06:09.602 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:06:09.602 --> 00:06:10.036 align:middle line:90%
>> ...got lost for...

00:06:10.036 --> 00:06:10.603 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:06:10.603 --> 00:06:11.571 align:middle line:90%
>> ...two weeks?

00:06:11.571 --> 00:06:12.105 align:middle line:84%
We didn't know where
the heck it was.

00:06:12.105 --> 00:06:12.906 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:06:12.906 --> 00:06:14.007 align:middle line:90%
We didn't know where it was.

00:06:14.007 --> 00:06:15.408 align:middle line:84%
>> Parked it in the
Gulf of Mexico, fire --

00:06:15.408 --> 00:06:17.744 align:middle line:84%
by the way, we don't have any
air defense systems along the

00:06:17.744 --> 00:06:19.179 align:middle line:90%
Gulf of Mexico.

00:06:19.179 --> 00:06:23.216 align:middle line:84%
We'd have less than five
minutes to react, then it's up.

00:06:23.216 --> 00:06:27.220 align:middle line:84%
>> How would we even
know who the culprit was?

00:06:27.220 --> 00:06:29.055 align:middle line:90%
>> There's another major point.

00:06:29.055 --> 00:06:31.925 align:middle line:84%
It's not going to be
like December 7th, 1941,

00:06:31.925 --> 00:06:33.426 align:middle line:84%
where our guys are
looking up and going,

00:06:33.426 --> 00:06:34.794 align:middle line:84%
"There's meatballs
on those planes.

00:06:34.794 --> 00:06:36.229 align:middle line:90%
It's the Japanese."

00:06:36.229 --> 00:06:39.265 align:middle line:84%
Or even on 911 where
we had the profile

00:06:39.265 --> 00:06:40.233 align:middle line:90%
within a matter of hours...

00:06:40.233 --> 00:06:40.934 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:06:40.934 --> 00:06:42.268 align:middle line:90%
>> ...this is al-Queda.

00:06:42.268 --> 00:06:44.838 align:middle line:84%
The cargo ship launches and
then it blows up and sinks?

00:06:44.838 --> 00:06:45.839 align:middle line:90%
These weapons...

00:06:45.839 --> 00:06:46.706 align:middle line:90%
>> And they're gone.

00:06:46.706 --> 00:06:47.540 align:middle line:84%
>> ...could have
been handed off?

00:06:47.540 --> 00:06:48.374 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:06:48.374 --> 00:06:49.442 align:middle line:90%
>> Who do we know has done it?

00:06:49.442 --> 00:06:51.678 align:middle line:90%
But it's a first-strike weapon.

00:06:51.678 --> 00:06:53.079 align:middle line:90%
That's the key thing.

00:06:53.079 --> 00:06:56.649 align:middle line:84%
It can take America down as a
major power player, cripple us,

00:06:56.649 --> 00:06:59.018 align:middle line:84%
and 90% of Americans
are dead a year later,

00:06:59.018 --> 00:07:00.553 align:middle line:84%
and we might not even
know where it came from.

00:07:00.553 --> 00:07:01.221 align:middle line:90%
>> Yet -- that's right.

00:07:01.221 --> 00:07:02.422 align:middle line:90%
We cannot retaliate.

00:07:02.422 --> 00:07:06.326 align:middle line:84%
We cannot, for example,
our subs, our nuclear subs

00:07:06.326 --> 00:07:09.128 align:middle line:84%
that have missiles on them
-- how do you detonate?

00:07:09.128 --> 00:07:10.763 align:middle line:84%
How do you launch
when you don't know

00:07:10.763 --> 00:07:12.532 align:middle line:90%
who you're launching against?

00:07:12.532 --> 00:07:13.366 align:middle line:90%
>> Correct.

00:07:13.366 --> 00:07:14.834 align:middle line:90%
And the North Korean profile --

00:07:14.834 --> 00:07:17.871 align:middle line:84%
the combination between
North Korea and Iran

00:07:17.871 --> 00:07:20.273 align:middle line:84%
with terrorist cells,
with the potential

00:07:20.273 --> 00:07:23.510 align:middle line:84%
of Nukes having disappeared
out of Russia in the last 10

00:07:23.510 --> 00:07:26.679 align:middle line:84%
to 15 years, that is
a deadly combination.

00:07:26.679 --> 00:07:31.117 align:middle line:84%
I am appalled with a policy that
allows North Korea to threaten

00:07:31.117 --> 00:07:34.654 align:middle line:84%
and to launch -- the
moment that missile crosses

00:07:34.654 --> 00:07:37.190 align:middle line:84%
into international
airspace, take it out.

00:07:37.190 --> 00:07:38.558 align:middle line:90%
>> Right, exactly.

00:07:38.558 --> 00:07:41.661 align:middle line:90%
And this is not just idle talk.

00:07:41.661 --> 00:07:45.298 align:middle line:84%
It's not rhetoric when
someone, as you just mentioned,

00:07:45.298 --> 00:07:49.636 align:middle line:84%
threatens your very
existence, creates videos

00:07:49.636 --> 00:07:51.271 align:middle line:90%
of your cities burning...

00:07:51.271 --> 00:07:51.905 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:07:51.905 --> 00:07:52.338 align:middle line:90%
>> ...in flames...

00:07:52.338 --> 00:07:53.540 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:55.275 align:middle line:84%
>> ...you know, you've got
to take that seriously.

00:07:55.275 --> 00:07:59.646 align:middle line:84%
And I really wonder what
someone like Putin would do

00:07:59.646 --> 00:08:02.782 align:middle line:84%
if the North Koreans
threatened Russia.

00:08:02.782 --> 00:08:05.418 align:middle line:84%
I think the guy would
have launched by now.

00:08:05.418 --> 00:08:09.589 align:middle line:84%
There are some nations out there
that just won't fool around,

00:08:09.589 --> 00:08:13.026 align:middle line:84%
yet we seem to -- look,
I spent nine years

00:08:13.026 --> 00:08:14.694 align:middle line:84%
as you know, William,
in the Navy.

00:08:14.694 --> 00:08:16.763 align:middle line:84%
I'm not a warmonger
by any means.

00:08:16.763 --> 00:08:18.398 align:middle line:90%
I hate war.

00:08:18.398 --> 00:08:20.300 align:middle line:90%
But you have to defend yourself.

00:08:20.300 --> 00:08:24.137 align:middle line:84%
And that's what a great
defense is supposed to do.

00:08:24.137 --> 00:08:28.107 align:middle line:84%
The government's role is to
defend the American people.

00:08:28.107 --> 00:08:32.344 align:middle line:84%
And when you have crazed
dictators screaming

00:08:32.344 --> 00:08:34.546 align:middle line:84%
