these rogue regimes, and say,

00:09:29.636 --> 00:09:31.838 align:middle line:84%
"Oh, they're really
not a threat."

00:09:31.838 --> 00:09:34.107 align:middle line:84%
And then the people who
are telling us that,

00:09:34.107 --> 00:09:35.308 align:middle line:84%
they go hide in the
high grass...

00:09:35.308 --> 00:09:35.975 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:09:35.975 --> 00:09:36.509 align:middle line:90%
>> ...a day later...

00:09:36.509 --> 00:09:37.577 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:09:37.577 --> 00:09:38.511 align:middle line:84%
>> ...when the world's
plunged into war.

00:09:38.511 --> 00:09:40.947 align:middle line:84%
We could recover
from Pearl Harbor.

00:09:40.947 --> 00:09:43.783 align:middle line:84%
We can recover and
we have from 911.

00:09:43.783 --> 00:09:47.687 align:middle line:84%
We cannot recover
within our lifetimes

00:09:47.687 --> 00:09:49.455 align:middle line:90%
if we're hit by an EMP strike.

00:09:49.455 --> 00:09:53.393 align:middle line:84%
It is a game ending -- it's
a first-strike game-ender.

00:09:53.393 --> 00:09:55.361 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, as you know, I
spend a lot of time going

00:09:55.361 --> 00:09:57.964 align:middle line:84%
between Los Angeles
and Saint Louis.

00:09:57.964 --> 00:10:01.100 align:middle line:84%
If you've ever been in the
Midwest during a tornado --

00:10:01.100 --> 00:10:03.336 align:middle line:84%
and I've seen the rubble
of Joplin, Missouri,

00:10:03.336 --> 00:10:05.905 align:middle line:84%
that had that tragedy
a few years ago --

00:10:05.905 --> 00:10:10.443 align:middle line:84%
if people go without
power for three days,

00:10:10.443 --> 00:10:12.512 align:middle line:90%
they start going nuts.

00:10:12.512 --> 00:10:16.749 align:middle line:84%
How long would it take -- and
we'll talk about the grid,

00:10:16.749 --> 00:10:17.917 align:middle line:90%
how long would it take

00:10:17.917 --> 00:10:21.754 align:middle line:84%
to get the power restored
under an EMP attack?

00:10:21.754 --> 00:10:22.855 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:10:22.855 --> 00:10:25.992 align:middle line:84%
>> We don't have backup
transformers, right?

00:10:25.992 --> 00:10:26.726 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:10:26.726 --> 00:10:28.194 align:middle line:90%
>> They're very big.

00:10:28.194 --> 00:10:30.596 align:middle line:84%
Probably some of them are
made in other countries.

00:10:30.596 --> 00:10:34.834 align:middle line:84%
It's not like you have one
readily available to move in.

00:10:34.834 --> 00:10:36.869 align:middle line:90%
How long would the power be out?

00:10:36.869 --> 00:10:39.472 align:middle line:84%
>> George, I attended a
conference several years ago,

00:10:39.472 --> 00:10:42.408 align:middle line:84%
upstate New York, Impact
America, which brought together

00:10:42.408 --> 00:10:45.044 align:middle line:84%
about a thousand
specialists on this topic.

00:10:45.044 --> 00:10:46.579 align:middle line:90%
It's not just the generators.

00:10:46.579 --> 00:10:49.882 align:middle line:84%
Okay. Let's take this glass and
say this is a power generator,

00:10:49.882 --> 00:10:52.852 align:middle line:84%
and the one over
there is your home.

00:10:52.852 --> 00:10:54.854 align:middle line:84%
There's a hundred miles
of high-tension wires...

00:10:54.854 --> 00:10:55.688 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:10:55.688 --> 00:10:56.622 align:middle line:90%
>> ...substations, and all that.

00:10:56.622 --> 00:10:58.891 align:middle line:90%
There is a major vulnerability.

00:10:58.891 --> 00:11:01.828 align:middle line:84%
I saw a frightful video of
what happens to those hundreds

00:11:01.828 --> 00:11:02.929 align:middle line:90%
of thousands of miles

00:11:02.929 --> 00:11:05.431 align:middle line:84%
of high-tension lines
under an EMP strike.

00:11:05.431 --> 00:11:06.199 align:middle line:90%
They explode.

00:11:06.199 --> 00:11:07.166 align:middle line:90%
>> They cook, don't they?

00:11:07.166 --> 00:11:08.134 align:middle line:84%
>> They -- no, right
off the pillars.

00:11:08.134 --> 00:11:09.469 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:11:09.469 --> 00:11:10.837 align:middle line:84%
>> So even if you were able
to preserve your generator,

00:11:10.837 --> 00:11:12.872 align:middle line:84%
which is doubtful,
even if you were able

00:11:12.872 --> 00:11:16.776 align:middle line:84%
to preserve your equipment
at home, which is doubtful,

00:11:16.776 --> 00:11:17.977 align:middle line:90%
you can't get the power out.

00:11:17.977 --> 00:11:19.512 align:middle line:84%
Here's a scary estimate
[two knocks].

00:11:19.512 --> 00:11:23.750 align:middle line:84%
At the conference a team
had evaluated 500 generating

00:11:23.750 --> 00:11:27.153 align:middle line:84%
systems, the major generating
systems east of the Mississippi.

00:11:27.153 --> 00:11:30.556 align:middle line:84%
80% will still be
offline five years later.

00:11:30.556 --> 00:11:31.758 align:middle line:90%
>> Five years later.

00:11:31.758 --> 00:11:34.060 align:middle line:84%
>> So imagine -- what's
the basis of our economy,

00:11:34.060 --> 00:11:36.729 align:middle line:84%
and we worry about our
economic times right now,

00:11:36.729 --> 00:11:42.435 align:middle line:84%
but imagine if we lost 80% of
our power capacity completely.

00:11:42.435 --> 00:11:43.002 align:middle line:90%
>> Frightening.

00:11:43.002 --> 00:11:44.003 align:middle line:90%
>> That is...

00:11:44.003 --> 00:11:46.239 align:middle line:84%
>> And we have an
old grid system...

00:11:46.239 --> 00:11:47.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Right, right.

00:11:47.640 --> 00:11:50.643 align:middle line:84%
>> ...that couldn't
withstand hardly anything.

00:11:50.643 --> 00:11:51.644 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:11:51.644 --> 00:11:53.813 align:middle line:84%
>> We've had power
outages before --

00:11:53.813 --> 00:11:55.882 align:middle line:90%
Canada, the Northeast...

00:11:55.882 --> 00:11:57.216 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:11:57.216 --> 00:12:00.119 align:middle line:84%
>> ...for a few days, for
weeks, caused by strange things

00:12:00.119 --> 00:12:03.756 align:middle line:84%
that have occurred -- power
transformers blowing up,

00:12:03.756 --> 00:12:06.626 align:middle line:84%
trees falling on wires,
and things like that.

00:12:06.626 --> 00:12:11.030 align:middle line:84%
Just a year ago in Southern
California, in that region,

00:12:11.030 --> 00:12:13.766 align:middle line:84%
three million people
without power.

00:12:13.766 --> 00:12:16.035 align:middle line:90%
We couldn't handle it.

00:12:16.035 --> 00:12:19.338 align:middle line:84%
>> All of the catastrophes
we have faced --

00:12:19.338 --> 00:12:21.841 align:middle line:90%
Katrina was a local event.

00:12:21.841 --> 00:12:23.242 align:middle line:84%
I live in Asheville,
North Carolina.

00:12:23.242 --> 00:12:24.410 align:middle line:90%
>> As tragic as it was.

00:12:24.410 --> 00:12:25.711 align:middle line:90%
>> As tragic as it was.

00:12:25.711 --> 00:12:28.881 align:middle line:84%
Within a day -- I teach at
a small Christian college --

00:12:28.881 --> 00:12:31.317 align:middle line:84%
we had truckloads
of supplies going

00:12:31.317 --> 00:12:34.086 align:middle line:84%
down to a sister
school in the area.

00:12:34.086 --> 00:12:37.456 align:middle line:84%
Trucks -- supplies were coming
in from all over the country.

00:12:37.456 --> 00:12:40.393 align:middle line:84%
What do you do when it's
the entire United States

00:12:40.393 --> 00:12:41.027 align:middle line:90%
that's down...

00:12:41.027 --> 00:12:42.128 align:middle line:90%
>> Can't do it.

00:12:42.128 --> 00:12:43.262 align:middle line:84%
>> ...and the transportation
grid is down,

00:12:43.262 --> 00:12:44.063 align:middle line:90%
and the communications...

00:12:44.063 --> 00:12:45.264 align:middle line:90%
>> You can't do it.

00:12:45.264 --> 00:12:46.766 align:middle line:84%
>> ...grid is down, and
the water supply is down,

00:12:46.766 --> 00:12:48.634 align:middle line:84%
and the food distribution
system is down,

00:12:48.634 --> 00:12:51.270 align:middle line:84%
and the medical supply
systems are down?

00:12:51.270 --> 00:12:52.438 align:middle line:90%
>> People will riot.

00:12:52.438 --> 00:12:53.139 align:middle line:90%
They'll go crazy.

00:12:53.139 --> 00:12:54.373 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes. Yes.

00:12:54.373 --> 00:12:56.008 align:middle line:84%
>> Let's take some questions
for William Forstchen.

00:12:56.008 --> 00:12:59.111 align:middle line:84%
Who's got some as
we talk about EMPs?

00:12:59.111 --> 00:13:01.047 align:middle line:84%
Right now we're talking
about it primarily

00:13:01.047 --> 00:13:02.982 align:middle line:90%
from some kind of an attack.

00:13:02.982 --> 00:13:04.183 align:middle line:90%
Yes, sir.

00:13:04.183 --> 00:13:05.818 align:middle line:84%
>> Thank you for
taking my question.

00:13:05.818 --> 00:13:10.356 align:middle line:84%
What can I do to protect my ham
radio, my vehicle, my generator

00:13:10.356 --> 00:13:12.024 align:middle line:90%
at home, to keep me up and going

00:13:12.024 --> 00:13:14.393 align:middle line:84%
when something like
this happens?

00:13:14.393 --> 00:13:15.895 align:middle line:84%
>> Give a highlight
William because we're going

00:13:15.895 --> 00:13:16.996 align:middle line:84%
to do a demonstration
at the end...

00:13:16.996 --> 00:13:18.030 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:13:18.030 --> 00:13:19.065 align:middle line:84%
>> ...of the program
on what he can do.

00:13:19.065 --> 00:13:22.068 align:middle line:84%
But it is fixable in
some cases, right?

00:13:22.068 --> 00:13:24.537 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes. Sir, it's
a great question.

00:13:24.537 --> 00:13:25.805 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:13:25.805 --> 00:13:29.575 align:middle line:84%
When I first started researching
the book I kept thinking

00:13:29.575 --> 00:13:30.910 align:middle line:90%
top-down response.

00:13:30.910 --> 00:13:34.514 align:middle line:84%
If only I can see our
federal government responding

00:13:34.514 --> 00:13:35.882 align:middle line:90%
and then state to local.

00:13:35.882 --> 00:13:39.819 align:middle line:84%
In the last couple of years
my view on that has changed.

00:13:39.819 --> 00:13:40.653 align:middle line:90%
It's about us.

00:13:40.653 --> 00:13:41.854 align:middle line:90%
It's about we, the people.

00:13:41.854 --> 00:13:44.457 align:middle line:84%
It's about Americans
being Americans,

00:13:44.457 --> 00:13:47.260 align:middle line:84%
which means we become
self-reliant.

00:13:47.260 --> 00:13:51.197 align:middle line:84%
And, sir, it's amazing the
number of start-up industries

00:13:51.197 --> 00:13:54.367 align:middle line:84%
within the last several years
addressing these type of issues.

00:13:54.367 --> 00:13:55.334 align:middle line:84%
We're going to demonstrate
a couple

00:13:55.334 --> 00:13:57.503 align:middle line:84%
of little items later
in the show.

00:13:57.503 --> 00:13:59.272 align:middle line:90%
There are a tremendous number

00:13:59.272 --> 00:14:02.008 align:middle line:84%
of things you can
do to be prepared.

00:14:02.008 --> 00:14:04.710 align:middle line:84%
One, to be able to get
through, say, the first 30 days

00:14:04.710 --> 00:14:08.681 align:middle line:84%
of any emergency, whether it's
EMP, earthquake, or whatever;

00:14:08.681 --> 00:14:10.716 align:middle line:84%
but also a little bit
of long-term planning.

00:14:10.716 --> 00:14:13.185 align:middle line:84%
And it's not expensive,
it's doable.

00:14:13.185 --> 00:14:16.122 align:middle line:84%
I have become convinced
that we, the people,

00:14:16.122 --> 00:14:17.590 align:middle line:90%
we have to act on our own.

00:14:17.590 --> 00:14:21.327 align:middle line:84%
Let's not worry about
FEMA coming to save us.

00:14:21.327 --> 00:14:24.730 align:middle line:84%
Let's work together as a
team that, if necessary,

00:14:24.730 --> 00:14:26.299 align:middle line:90%
we can rebuild our country.

00:14:26.299 --> 00:14:31.203 align:middle line:84%
>> Is the bottom line,
William, we're just up a creek

00:14:31.203 --> 00:14:35.741 align:middle line:84%
if something like this happens,
and what we really need to do is

00:14:35.741 --> 00:14:39.912 align:middle line:84%
to just make sure that
these rogue nations don't do

00:14:39.912 --> 00:14:41.414 align:middle line:90%
anything stupid?

00:14:41.414 --> 00:14:44.917 align:middle line:84%
Case in point; you know,
we've been in the nuclear era

00:14:44.917 --> 00:14:47.553 align:middle line:90%
with Russia for 60 years.

00:14:47.553 --> 00:14:49.822 align:middle line:90%
China has joined the club.

00:14:49.822 --> 00:14:52.325 align:middle line:90%
Not one has launched.

00:14:52.325 --> 00:14:55.795 align:middle line:84%
They're smart enough to know
that if they do we're going

00:14:55.795 --> 00:14:59.098 align:middle line:84%
to retaliate in a big
way, and everybody loses.

00:14:59.098 --> 00:15:00.499 align:middle line:90%
But some of these lunatics,

00:15:00.499 --> 00:15:02.635 align:middle line:84%
these rogue nations
we've been talking about,

00:15:02.635 --> 00:15:04.337 align:middle line:90%
who would do these things

00:15:04.337 --> 00:15:07.573 align:middle line:84%
in a clandestine
way, they don't care.

00:15:07.573 --> 00:15:11.243 align:middle line:84%
It's almost as if they
have nothing to lose.

00:15:11.243 --> 00:15:14.847 align:middle line:84%
Those are the entities we
have to be concerned about.

00:15:14.847 --> 00:15:20.886 align:middle line:84%
And, honestly, we need to just
take the nuclear capabilities

00:15:20.886 --> 00:15:22.221 align:middle line:90%
out of their hands.

00:15:22.221 --> 00:15:25.257 align:middle line:90%
>> You hit the core issue.

00:15:25.257 --> 00:15:29.328 align:middle line:84%
Ever since the soviets
acquired nuclear devices in 1949

00:15:29.328 --> 00:15:31.097 align:middle line:84%
and we got into the
arms race and a couple

00:15:31.097 --> 00:15:35.167 align:middle line:84%
of us are old enough to remember
the Cold War and Duck and Cover,

00:15:35.167 --> 00:15:37.603 align:middle line:84%
we had what was called
"mutual assured destruction."

00:15:37.603 --> 00:15:38.804 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:15:38.804 --> 00:15:41.974 align:middle line:84%
>> If the Soviets launched
at us it's a no-win game

00:15:41.974 --> 00:15:44.176 align:middle line:84%
because enough of our
assets will survive

00:15:44.176 --> 00:15:47.480 align:middle line:84%
that we will launch back and
I actually say, you know,

00:15:47.480 --> 00:15:49.415 align:middle line:84%
I'm kind of glad the
Soviets are atheists

00:15:49.415 --> 00:15:52.585 align:middle line:84%
because they were pragmatic
about it, they did not want

00:15:52.585 --> 00:15:55.888 align:middle line:84%
to inherit a smoking
ruined world.

00:15:55.888 --> 00:15:57.356 align:middle line:90%
So it was a no-win scenario.

00:15:57.356 --> 00:16:01.360 align:middle line:84%
So, therefore, against these
nations there was not a launch.

00:16:01.360 --> 00:16:04.964 align:middle line:84%
But we are dealing with Iran
where their leader talks

00:16:04.964 --> 00:16:08.267 align:middle line:90%
down a well to a hidden ahmad

00:16:08.267 --> 00:16:10.336 align:middle line:84%
who is supposedly is
telling him, "end the world."

00:16:10.336 --> 00:16:11.137 align:middle line:90%
>> End the world.

00:16:11.137 --> 00:16:12.138 align:middle line:90%
>> End the world.

00:16:12.138 --> 00:16:13.472 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:16:13.472 --> 00:16:18.444 align:middle line:84%
>> And we have a wacko psycho
in Korea who might decide,

00:16:18.444 --> 00:16:21.013 align:middle line:84%
"I'm going to destroy America
just for the hell of it today."

00:16:21.013 --> 00:16:22.381 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:16:22.381 --> 00:16:24.517 align:middle line:84%
>> Neutral shore destruction
doesn't work with these people.

00:16:24.517 --> 00:16:27.820 align:middle line:84%
The only thing that does work is
a very aggressive foreign policy

00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:30.356 align:middle line:84%
statement upfront, "Don't
even contemplate it."

00:16:30.356 --> 00:16:31.123 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:16:31.123 --> 00:16:31.791 align:middle line:90%
>> "We'll stop you first."

00:16:31.791 --> 00:16:33.125 align:middle line:90%
>> And this is why.

00:16:33.125 --> 00:16:35.394 align:middle line:84%
Don't. Let's take another
question for William Forstchen.

00:16:35.394 --> 00:16:37.129 align:middle line:90%
Yes sir, way in the back here.

00:16:37.129 --> 00:16:38.397 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:16:38.397 --> 00:16:42.034 align:middle line:84%
William, could you assess
the danger and probability

00:16:42.034 --> 00:16:46.338 align:middle line:84%
of a terrorist group
using a non-nuclear device

00:16:46.338 --> 00:16:48.107 align:middle line:90%
to induce an EMP?

00:16:48.107 --> 00:16:50.242 align:middle line:84%
See, I would rank that as
being a much more highly,

00:16:50.242 --> 00:16:55.147 align:middle line:84%
more probable event than
using a nuclear device.

00:16:55.147 --> 00:16:56.348 align:middle line:90%
>> That's a good point, sir.

00:16:56.348 --> 00:16:59.485 align:middle line:84%
EMP can be generated a
number of different ways.

00:16:59.485 --> 00:17:01.720 align:middle line:84%
For example, you can
just go on YouTube,

00:17:01.720 --> 00:17:05.091 align:middle line:90%
just look up Ford Taurus EMP,

00:17:05.091 --> 00:17:09.862 align:middle line:84%
and you'll see a car that's
toasted up by a non-nuclear EMP.

00:17:09.862 --> 00:17:15.167 align:middle line:84%
The strategic drawback
to a non-nuclear EMP is

00:17:15.167 --> 00:17:18.604 align:middle line:84%
at best you can generate
a blocks-wide,

00:17:18.604 --> 00:17:21.739 align:middle line:90%
perhaps partial city event.

00:17:21.739 --> 00:17:24.110 align:middle line:90%
Whereas, the nuke can...

00:17:24.110 --> 00:17:25.143 align:middle line:90%
>> Can generate...

00:17:25.143 --> 00:17:27.480 align:middle line:84%
>> ...a country-wide
continental event.

00:17:27.480 --> 00:17:30.883 align:middle line:84%
So, in terms of particularly
tactical uses, an EMP,

00:17:30.883 --> 00:17:34.720 align:middle line:84%
non-nuke -- in fact,
they're already out there.

00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:38.224 align:middle line:84%
The one that we have to be very
concerned about is the nuke

00:17:38.224 --> 00:17:42.094 align:middle line:84%
which can take out the entire
United States or Europe.

00:17:42.094 --> 00:17:45.097 align:middle line:84%
And the perfect scenario
for our foes is to put three

00:17:45.097 --> 00:17:49.101 align:middle line:84%
up over the United States:
East, Midwest, West;

00:17:49.101 --> 00:17:50.970 align:middle line:84%
lay down a blanket
across the continent,

00:17:50.970 --> 00:17:52.338 align:middle line:90%
take the whole grid out.

00:17:52.338 --> 00:17:56.008 align:middle line:84%
>> And the damage from a
non-nuke is not, as you said,

00:17:56.008 --> 00:17:58.811 align:middle line:84%
not as wide-spread
but it's also not

00:17:58.811 --> 00:18:00.479 align:middle line:90%
that effective in the region.

00:18:00.479 --> 00:18:01.914 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't cook everything...

00:18:01.914 --> 00:18:02.548 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:18:02.548 --> 00:18:02.982 align:middle line:90%
>> ...for example.

00:18:02.982 --> 00:18:03.816 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:18:03.816 --> 00:18:05.184 align:middle line:90%
>> We've got high technology.

00:18:05.184 --> 00:18:07.987 align:middle line:84%
Let's go to one of our video
questions for William Forstchen.

00:18:07.987 --> 00:18:09.121 align:middle line:90%
>> Hey, William.

00:18:09.121 --> 00:18:10.489 align:middle line:90%
This is Josh from Brooklyn,

00:18:10.489 --> 00:18:14.493 align:middle line:84%
and I was wondering how real
is the threat of an EMP attack?

00:18:14.493 --> 00:18:15.561 align:middle line:90%
>> Well...

00:18:15.561 --> 00:18:16.695 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, that's a
great question, Josh.

00:18:16.695 --> 00:18:17.396 align:middle line:90%
>> It really is.

00:18:17.396 --> 00:18:18.197 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello from Brooklyn.

00:18:18.197 --> 00:18:20.833 align:middle line:90%
I grew up outside of Newark.

00:18:20.833 --> 00:18:22.334 align:middle line:90%
It is real.

00:18:22.334 --> 00:18:26.105 align:middle line:84%
There was a very
clear statement made

00:18:26.105 --> 00:18:28.641 align:middle line:90%
in the 2004 Congressional study

00:18:28.641 --> 00:18:31.744 align:middle line:84%
which is another source I would
recommend people to go to.

00:18:31.744 --> 00:18:36.415 align:middle line:84%
Just simply Google 2004
Congressional EMP Commission

00:18:36.415 --> 00:18:38.517 align:middle line:90%
to get the full report.

00:18:38.517 --> 00:18:43.956 align:middle line:84%
One of the experts on it
said, "I cannot predict when,

00:18:43.956 --> 00:18:45.891 align:middle line:84%
but I can tell you
it will happen."

00:18:45.891 --> 00:18:46.926 align:middle line:90%
>> It will happen eventually.

00:18:46.926 --> 00:18:48.394 align:middle line:90%
>> Most likely in our lifetime.

00:18:48.394 --> 00:18:53.465 align:middle line:84%
But then added on in the 2008
report, "When it comes to CME,

00:18:53.465 --> 00:18:55.968 align:middle line:84%
a solar event which basically
triggers the same type

00:18:55.968 --> 00:18:58.837 align:middle line:84%
of phenomena, that
is inevitable.

00:18:58.837 --> 00:19:00.739 align:middle line:84%
And the odds are running
down on us right now.

00:19:00.739 --> 00:19:01.974 align:middle line:90%
>> I think you're right.

00:19:01.974 --> 00:19:03.642 align:middle line:84%
Let's take one more question
for William Forstchen.

00:19:03.642 --> 00:19:04.743 align:middle line:90%
Yes, sir, right here.

00:19:04.743 --> 00:19:06.779 align:middle line:84%
>> William, we don't
hear very much about it

00:19:06.779 --> 00:19:08.447 align:middle line:90%
in the mainstream media.

00:19:08.447 --> 00:19:11.717 align:middle line:84%
Is it being suppressed
by the U.S. Government?

00:19:12.985 --> 00:19:16.922 align:middle line:84%
>> Let's just say if
we don't talk about it,

00:19:16.922 --> 00:19:18.490 align:middle line:84%
you're not going
to worry about it.

00:19:18.490 --> 00:19:20.826 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to get into
the political side on this,

00:19:20.826 --> 00:19:24.430 align:middle line:84%
but I think all of us at times
feel tremendous frustration

00:19:24.430 --> 00:19:27.433 align:middle line:84%
when we see what we think is a
very crucial news item related

00:19:27.433 --> 00:19:30.936 align:middle line:84%
to national defense, foreign
policy, that gets buried

00:19:30.936 --> 00:19:35.808 align:middle line:84%
under because some starlet
had another drunken brawl

00:19:35.808 --> 00:19:37.109 align:middle line:90%
or whatever [laughter].

00:19:37.109 --> 00:19:42.114 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to go near
that any further, all right?

00:19:42.114 --> 00:19:44.783 align:middle line:84%
One of the problems,
as conveyed to me

00:19:44.783 --> 00:19:47.886 align:middle line:84%
by a remarkable congressman,
Congressman Roscoe Bartlett

00:19:47.886 --> 00:19:51.457 align:middle line:84%
out of Maryland, who asked
me to write this book --

00:19:51.457 --> 00:19:53.025 align:middle line:84%
and he just so happened
to be gerrymandered

00:19:53.025 --> 00:19:55.094 align:middle line:84%
out in the last election
-- is to build a --

00:19:55.094 --> 00:19:58.731 align:middle line:84%
the problem with EMP is
there's no constituency.

00:19:58.731 --> 00:20:00.432 align:middle line:90%
Very few people know about it.

00:20:00.432 --> 00:20:01.800 align:middle line:90%
For example, do you know

00:20:01.800 --> 00:20:04.770 align:middle line:84%
that Congress several years
back passed a law forbidding us

00:20:04.770 --> 00:20:06.438 align:middle line:90%
from owning chimpanzees?

00:20:06.438 --> 00:20:10.242 align:middle line:90%
I'd ask the audience, why?

00:20:10.242 --> 00:20:12.077 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's because of
that horrible attack.

00:20:12.077 --> 00:20:13.145 align:middle line:90%
Remember several years ago...

00:20:13.145 --> 00:20:14.146 align:middle line:84%
>> Of that -- ripped
off the lady's face.

00:20:14.146 --> 00:20:14.580 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:20:14.580 --> 00:20:15.714 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:20:15.714 --> 00:20:17.016 align:middle line:84%
>> So, George, if you
ever drop over my house,

00:20:17.016 --> 00:20:18.050 align:middle line:90%
the chimpanzee is gone.

00:20:18.050 --> 00:20:19.051 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
worry about it.

00:20:19.051 --> 00:20:20.219 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't have to
worry about that.

00:20:20.219 --> 00:20:21.687 align:middle line:84%
>> You don't have to
worry about that any more.

00:20:21.687 --> 00:20:23.355 align:middle line:90%
Now, yes, we needed that law,

00:20:23.355 --> 00:20:24.923 align:middle line:84%
but how many people
does it affect?

00:20:24.923 --> 00:20:25.691 align:middle line:90%
One or two?

00:20:25.691 --> 00:20:26.959 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:20:26.959 --> 00:20:28.961 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, Congress and Bartlett
for 12 years kept trying

00:20:28.961 --> 00:20:32.731 align:middle line:84%
to get something done on EMP
but nobody was paying attention.

00:20:32.731 --> 00:20:35.968 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like if you talk
about EMPing in your forest

00:20:35.968 --> 00:20:37.569 align:middle line:84%
and the trees are
falling as well,

00:20:37.569 --> 00:20:40.773 align:middle line:84%
and the media isn't
there, it doesn't exist.

00:20:40.773 --> 00:20:42.207 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you know,
let's talk for a moment

00:20:42.207 --> 00:20:45.277 align:middle line:84%
about the Boston Marathon
bombing that just occurred.

00:20:45.277 --> 00:20:50.783 align:middle line:84%
Who would have suspected
a couple thugs

00:20:50.783 --> 00:20:56.255 align:middle line:84%
to put pressure cookers loaded
with bomb-making material

00:20:56.255 --> 00:21:01.260 align:middle line:84%
in a knapsack and blow up
the region there, you know,

00:21:01.260 --> 00:21:04.797 align:middle line:84%
and kill the number of people
and injure hundreds of others?

00:21:04.797 --> 00:21:07.700 align:middle line:90%
Who would have expected that?

00:21:07.700 --> 00:21:08.567 align:middle line:90%
But it happened..

00:21:08.567 --> 00:21:09.902 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, it did.

00:21:09.902 --> 00:21:11.270 align:middle line:84%
>> And I think it's
the same thing

00:21:11.270 --> 00:21:14.306 align:middle line:90%
with a nuke and an EMP attack.

00:21:14.306 --> 00:21:17.276 align:middle line:84%
One may not think
it's going to happen.

00:21:17.276 --> 00:21:20.379 align:middle line:84%
One may not hope
it's going to happen.

00:21:20.379 --> 00:21:24.183 align:middle line:84%
But one day some moron,
some idiot, is going to use

00:21:24.183 --> 00:21:27.720 align:middle line:84%
that capability and
try it and test it.

00:21:27.720 --> 00:21:32.291 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we need to
be alert for because our way

00:21:32.291 --> 00:21:34.727 align:middle line:90%
of living is over when...

00:21:34.727 --> 00:21:35.694 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:21:35.694 --> 00:21:36.729 align:middle line:84%
>> ...something like
that happens.

00:21:36.729 --> 00:21:38.464 align:middle line:84%
>> George, and you
notice, for example,

00:21:38.464 --> 00:21:41.133 align:middle line:84%
let's deal with the real
horrible tragedy recently

00:21:41.133 --> 00:21:44.903 align:middle line:84%
of Newtown or what happened
just outside of Denver...

00:21:44.903 --> 00:21:45.471 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:21:45.471 --> 00:21:46.872 align:middle line:90%
>> ...in Aurora.

00:21:46.872 --> 00:21:50.275 align:middle line:84%
How the day after the event we
keep saying, "If only, if only,

00:21:50.275 --> 00:21:53.312 align:middle line:84%
if only we had done this,
if only we had done that."

00:21:53.312 --> 00:21:57.316 align:middle line:84%
And, again, the problem with EMP
is there's no room for saying

00:21:57.316 --> 00:21:58.384 align:middle line:90%
"if only" the day after the...

00:21:58.384 --> 00:21:59.785 align:middle line:90%
>> You've got one chance.

00:21:59.785 --> 00:22:01.053 align:middle line:90%
>> ...event.

00:22:01.053 --> 00:22:04.256 align:middle line:84%
And it is to prepare
individually if it is going

00:22:04.256 --> 00:22:08.327 align:middle line:84%
to happen, but then also
prepare as a nation to convey

00:22:08.327 --> 00:22:09.461 align:middle line:90%
"don't even think about it

00:22:09.461 --> 00:22:12.865 align:middle line:84%
because we will stop you
in any way possible."

00:22:12.865 --> 00:22:15.634 align:middle line:84%
>> Let's talk about the sun
and a coronal mass ejection.

00:22:15.634 --> 00:22:17.202 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, we can't stop the
sun from doing this, right.

00:22:17.202 --> 00:22:18.670 align:middle line:90%
>> And then the possibilities.

00:22:18.670 --> 00:22:21.974 align:middle line:84%
You had said 90% of
the population dies.

00:22:21.974 --> 00:22:23.075 align:middle line:90%
I want you to paint

00:22:23.075 --> 00:22:25.144 align:middle line:84%
that scenario a little
bit later on for us.

00:22:25.144 --> 00:22:28.380 align:middle line:84%
And just take it through us, and
let's assume something happens,

00:22:28.380 --> 00:22:31.417 align:middle line:84%
and I want you to tell us
what's going on on the planet,

00:22:31.417 --> 00:22:32.985 align:middle line:90%
how will we reacting,

00:22:32.985 --> 00:22:36.188 align:middle line:84%
what systems are collapsing,
and how people react.

00:22:36.188 --> 00:22:39.191 align:middle line:84%
But the sun, we cannot
stop that.

00:22:39.191 --> 00:22:42.261 align:middle line:84%
One day, in X-flare
-- we've been lucky.

00:22:42.261 --> 00:22:46.365 align:middle line:84%
You know, we have smaller class
flares, then M-class flares,

00:22:46.365 --> 00:22:50.135 align:middle line:84%
and then the big ones: the
X-flares, which are then X-1

00:22:50.135 --> 00:22:52.404 align:middle line:90%
up to [inaudible], X-15 or 20.

00:22:52.404 --> 00:22:53.172 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:22:53.172 --> 00:22:54.406 align:middle line:90%
>> The higher that number

00:22:54.406 --> 00:22:57.676 align:middle line:84%
on the X-scale the more
deadly it is for the planet.

00:22:57.676 --> 00:22:59.311 align:middle line:90%
We've been lucky.

00:22:59.311 --> 00:23:03.649 align:middle line:84%
Most of the big flares of recent
times have shot off toward

00:23:03.649 --> 00:23:04.817 align:middle line:90%
the side.

00:23:04.817 --> 00:23:07.619 align:middle line:84%
We weren't in direct
relationship with the sun.

00:23:07.619 --> 00:23:11.323 align:middle line:84%
But the day's going to come
when the sun's going to be there

00:23:11.323 --> 00:23:14.860 align:middle line:84%
and we're going to be here and
it's going to be a perfect shot.

00:23:14.860 --> 00:23:18.931 align:middle line:84%
And if it's a big one, my radio
show's knocked off the air,

00:23:18.931 --> 00:23:20.599 align:middle line:90%
and a lot of other things.

00:23:20.599 --> 00:23:21.166 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:23:21.166 --> 00:23:22.201 align:middle line:90%
>> That quick.

00:23:22.201 --> 00:23:23.569 align:middle line:90%
If that happens, it's gone.

00:23:23.569 --> 00:23:24.937 align:middle line:90%
>> It's over for all of us.

00:23:24.937 --> 00:23:25.838 align:middle line:84%
>> What am I going to -- well,
what am I going to do later?

00:23:25.838 --> 00:23:26.805 align:middle line:90%
>> I know.

00:23:26.805 --> 00:23:27.739 align:middle line:84%
What do you do when
it's all done?

00:23:27.739 --> 00:23:28.841 align:middle line:84%
>> I'll just stare
at the ceiling.

00:23:28.841 --> 00:23:31.343 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean, that's a
very real possibility.

00:23:31.343 --> 00:23:32.478 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:23:32.478 --> 00:23:35.247 align:middle line:84%
>> How do you protect
on something like that?

00:23:35.247 --> 00:23:38.750 align:middle line:84%
>> That is a scary
question because --

00:23:38.750 --> 00:23:42.754 align:middle line:84%
let us say the United States
endured an EMP strike.

00:23:42.754 --> 00:23:44.089 align:middle line:90%
We still, I'd like to think,

00:23:44.089 --> 00:23:46.158 align:middle line:84%
have some friends
around the world...

00:23:46.158 --> 00:23:47.159 align:middle line:90%
>> Who will jump in and help.

00:23:47.159 --> 00:23:48.427 align:middle line:90%
>> ...who will jump in.

00:23:48.427 --> 00:23:51.530 align:middle line:84%
However, most of all our
high-end electronic equipment

00:23:51.530 --> 00:23:53.232 align:middle line:84%
for power distribution
and everything else --

00:23:53.232 --> 00:23:54.867 align:middle line:90%
guess where it's made?

00:23:54.867 --> 00:23:56.201 align:middle line:90%
>> China.

00:23:56.201 --> 00:23:57.236 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah. Do you think they're
really going to rush boats

00:23:57.236 --> 00:23:59.304 align:middle line:84%
over with, "Oh, we
wish to help you."?

00:23:59.304 --> 00:24:01.607 align:middle line:84%
But now let's consider
a global event.

00:24:01.607 --> 00:24:02.708 align:middle line:90%
Now you remember, the closer

00:24:02.708 --> 00:24:04.977 align:middle line:84%
to the Pole you get
the more intense it is.

00:24:04.977 --> 00:24:06.378 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:24:06.378 --> 00:24:08.013 align:middle line:84%
>> The Carrington Event would
most likely have taken things

00:24:08.013 --> 00:24:12.084 align:middle line:84%
out all the way down to 25
degrees South, 25 degrees North.

00:24:12.084 --> 00:24:14.219 align:middle line:84%
>> But they didn't have a lot
of electronics in those days.

00:24:14.219 --> 00:24:15.387 align:middle line:90%
There was just a telegraph.

00:24:15.387 --> 00:24:15.888 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:24:15.888 --> 00:24:17.122 align:middle line:90%
>> Right?

00:24:17.122 --> 00:24:21.093 align:middle line:84%
>> So imagine a global-wide
shutdown of power grids

00:24:21.093 --> 00:24:22.628 align:middle line:90%
and systems going offline.

00:24:22.628 --> 00:24:23.328 align:middle line:90%
>> No image.

00:24:23.328 --> 00:24:23.962 align:middle line:90%
>> If you remember that.

00:24:23.962 --> 00:24:24.463 align:middle line:90%
>> No television.

00:24:24.463 --> 00:24:24.997 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:24:24.997 --> 00:24:26.098 align:middle line:90%
>> No radio.

00:24:26.098 --> 00:24:26.798 align:middle line:84%
>> No [multiple voices]
command and control.

00:24:26.798 --> 00:24:27.366 align:middle line:90%
>> No communications.

00:24:27.366 --> 00:24:27.900 align:middle line:90%
No cell phones.

00:24:27.900 --> 00:24:28.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:24:28.600 --> 00:24:29.701 align:middle line:90%
>> No text messaging.

00:24:29.701 --> 00:24:31.904 align:middle line:90%
Nothing. Everything's gone.

00:24:31.904 --> 00:24:35.474 align:middle line:84%
Every store is tied into
some form of electronics.

00:24:35.474 --> 00:24:37.309 align:middle line:90%
There was a power outage

00:24:37.309 --> 00:24:40.879 align:middle line:84%
in Saint Louis last
year, lasted six hours.

00:24:40.879 --> 00:24:44.883 align:middle line:84%
A local drugstore chain --
the power was knocked out.

00:24:44.883 --> 00:24:46.985 align:middle line:90%
They tried to do it manually.

00:24:46.985 --> 00:24:48.687 align:middle line:90%
Number one, the young kids

00:24:48.687 --> 00:24:53.225 align:middle line:84%
who were working there couldn't
subtract in their heads.

00:24:53.225 --> 00:24:57.162 align:middle line:84%
If, you know, somebody gave you
a 20 and your bill was 8.68,

00:24:57.162 --> 00:25:01.300 align:middle line:84%
they didn't know that
it was 11.32 in change.

00:25:01.300 --> 00:25:03.335 align:middle line:90%
People were lined up like crazy.

00:25:03.335 --> 00:25:04.436 align:middle line:90%
It was a disaster.

00:25:04.436 --> 00:25:06.438 align:middle line:90%
They shut the store down.

00:25:06.438 --> 00:25:08.273 align:middle line:90%
That would happen too.

00:25:08.273 --> 00:25:11.510 align:middle line:84%
They don't have cash registers
that function anymore.

00:25:11.510 --> 00:25:13.345 align:middle line:84%
You don't have the
old-style anymore

00:25:13.345 --> 00:25:15.414 align:middle line:84%
where the lady would
push the button

00:25:15.414 --> 00:25:18.216 align:middle line:90%
and it would register on print.

00:25:18.216 --> 00:25:19.818 align:middle line:84%
Everything's electronic,
everything.

00:25:19.818 --> 00:25:23.889 align:middle line:84%
>> Right. What do you
guys have in your wallets?

00:25:23.889 --> 00:25:24.690 align:middle line:90%
>> Credit cards.

00:25:24.690 --> 00:25:25.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:25:25.390 --> 00:25:26.091 align:middle line:90%
>> You can't use them.

00:25:26.091 --> 00:25:26.725 align:middle line:90%
>> Several weeks ago...

00:25:26.725 --> 00:25:27.426 align:middle line:90%
>> ATMs.

00:25:27.426 --> 00:25:28.126 align:middle line:90%
>> You remember Cypress?

00:25:28.126 --> 00:25:28.961 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:25:28.961 --> 00:25:30.429 align:middle line:90%
>> Where they had the bank panic

00:25:30.429 --> 00:25:32.230 align:middle line:84%
and then they shut
down all the ATMs...

00:25:32.230 --> 00:25:33.265 align:middle line:90%
>> All the ATMs.

00:25:33.265 --> 00:25:35.567 align:middle line:90%
>> ...and people were panicked.

00:25:35.567 --> 00:25:39.871 align:middle line:84%
And in a post-EMP
or CME scenario --

00:25:39.871 --> 00:25:42.074 align:middle line:84%
within a matter of hours
people are going to be going,

00:25:42.074 --> 00:25:44.276 align:middle line:84%
"I better get my money
out of the bank."

00:25:44.276 --> 00:25:45.410 align:middle line:90%
Well, guess what?

00:25:45.410 --> 00:25:46.778 align:middle line:84%
Almost all our money
is electronic.

00:25:46.778 --> 00:25:47.346 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:25:47.346 --> 00:25:48.347 align:middle line:90%
>> It is gone.

00:25:48.347 --> 00:25:50.082 align:middle line:84%
>> And even if you
