It's enriched our
lives in so many ways.

00:34:04.109 --> 00:34:07.311 align:middle line:84%
But we have not caught up
with the vulnerabilities

00:34:07.311 --> 00:34:09.646 align:middle line:84%
to those systems
at the same time.

00:34:09.646 --> 00:34:11.349 align:middle line:84%
That is the message
you're getting

00:34:11.349 --> 00:34:12.817 align:middle line:90%
out that I'm so grateful for.

00:34:12.817 --> 00:34:16.954 align:middle line:84%
>> Part of me, part of me
would like to see the sun kick

00:34:16.954 --> 00:34:18.690 align:middle line:90%
out an X-flare that would...

00:34:18.690 --> 00:34:20.125 align:middle line:90%
>> He's saying this, not me.

00:34:20.125 --> 00:34:24.195 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm saying this -- that would
hit a region of this planet

00:34:24.195 --> 00:34:26.831 align:middle line:90%
that might not be too inhabited,

00:34:26.831 --> 00:34:30.934 align:middle line:84%
but enough to make the
world look at what happened;

00:34:30.934 --> 00:34:32.170 align:middle line:90%
and maybe it would take

00:34:32.170 --> 00:34:35.974 align:middle line:84%
out whatever power was
there and things like that.

00:34:35.974 --> 00:34:37.474 align:middle line:90%
We need an example.

00:34:37.474 --> 00:34:40.311 align:middle line:84%
We need people to
look at this and say,

00:34:40.311 --> 00:34:42.680 align:middle line:90%
"This is a real possibility."

00:34:42.680 --> 00:34:46.151 align:middle line:84%
And I think most politicians,
William, stick their heads

00:34:46.151 --> 00:34:49.186 align:middle line:84%
in the sand and they say,
"This is not going to happen

00:34:49.186 --> 00:34:51.889 align:middle line:84%
on my watch so I don't
have to worry about it."

00:34:51.889 --> 00:34:54.125 align:middle line:84%
Well, let the guy in the
future worry about it.

00:34:54.125 --> 00:34:55.492 align:middle line:90%
Well, you know what?

00:34:55.492 --> 00:34:59.230 align:middle line:84%
I just came back from Saint
Louis, saw my six grandchildren

00:34:59.230 --> 00:35:02.734 align:middle line:84%
and my three kids,
and I don't want this

00:35:02.734 --> 00:35:05.670 align:middle line:90%
to happen to them, you know?

00:35:05.670 --> 00:35:07.472 align:middle line:84%
Whether it happens
in my lifetime

00:35:07.472 --> 00:35:09.073 align:middle line:90%
or not is not the issue.

00:35:09.073 --> 00:35:11.976 align:middle line:90%
What about them and their kids?

00:35:11.976 --> 00:35:13.978 align:middle line:84%
And we're not doing
anything for them.

00:35:13.978 --> 00:35:15.380 align:middle line:90%
And we need to.

00:35:15.380 --> 00:35:18.583 align:middle line:84%
>> The inspiration for writing
the book came from many sources,

00:35:18.583 --> 00:35:20.919 align:middle line:90%
and one of them was I'm sitting

00:35:20.919 --> 00:35:23.154 align:middle line:84%
up on the stage on
graduation day.

00:35:23.154 --> 00:35:25.156 align:middle line:84%
I teach history at
a small college.

00:35:25.156 --> 00:35:27.225 align:middle line:90%
I'm looking at my students.

00:35:27.225 --> 00:35:29.594 align:middle line:84%
And I will tell you I
got a lump in my throat,

00:35:29.594 --> 00:35:31.029 align:middle line:90%
and that was actually --

00:35:31.029 --> 00:35:33.097 align:middle line:84%
that's when I started
writing the book, that night.

00:35:33.097 --> 00:35:34.666 align:middle line:84%
What's going to happen
to my kids?

00:35:34.666 --> 00:35:36.134 align:middle line:90%
They become your kids.

00:35:36.134 --> 00:35:38.970 align:middle line:84%
These wonderful 21,
20 year olds,

00:35:38.970 --> 00:35:40.705 align:middle line:84%
who are just graduating
from college.

00:35:40.705 --> 00:35:41.506 align:middle line:90%
What's going to happen to my...

00:35:41.506 --> 00:35:42.707 align:middle line:90%
>> Let's hope.

00:35:42.707 --> 00:35:43.141 align:middle line:84%
>> ...what's going to
happen to my little girl?

00:35:43.141 --> 00:35:44.275 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:35:44.275 --> 00:35:45.476 align:middle line:84%
>> I want America to be
better for my children

00:35:45.476 --> 00:35:47.979 align:middle line:84%
and grandchildren than
the America my father

00:35:47.979 --> 00:35:48.880 align:middle line:90%
and mother gave to me.

00:35:48.880 --> 00:35:49.747 align:middle line:90%
>> It's a nightmare.

00:35:49.747 --> 00:35:50.415 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:35:50.415 --> 00:35:51.482 align:middle line:90%
>> It's a nightmare.

00:35:51.482 --> 00:35:54.285 align:middle line:84%
It's almost a mass
extinction situation.

00:35:54.285 --> 00:35:58.089 align:middle line:84%
>> It would be a mass
extinction event.

00:35:58.089 --> 00:36:00.625 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we are going to
get into the possibilities

00:36:00.625 --> 00:36:03.494 align:middle line:84%
of what we might be
able to do to minimize

00:36:03.494 --> 00:36:06.030 align:middle line:84%
that which is really
so important.

00:36:06.030 --> 00:36:08.866 align:middle line:84%
But what got you
to write this book?

00:36:08.866 --> 00:36:11.336 align:middle line:84%
What was the first
thing that came to you?

00:36:11.336 --> 00:36:14.405 align:middle line:84%
I mean, were you an expert in
EMPs when you started this?

00:36:14.405 --> 00:36:19.143 align:middle line:84%
>> I studied -- as I mentioned
I got my PhD at Purdue,

00:36:19.143 --> 00:36:22.080 align:middle line:84%
military history,
history technology.

00:36:22.080 --> 00:36:27.485 align:middle line:84%
I was aware of the strategic
combat use of EMP in the event

00:36:27.485 --> 00:36:29.754 align:middle line:90%
of a war with the Soviet Union.

00:36:29.754 --> 00:36:35.827 align:middle line:84%
And back in '04 the
commission report came out.

00:36:35.827 --> 00:36:41.199 align:middle line:84%
That's what hit me -- Meeting
Congressman Roscoe Bartlett

00:36:41.199 --> 00:36:44.335 align:middle line:84%
who lamented to me, "Nobody
paid attention to this report."

00:36:44.335 --> 00:36:45.336 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:36:45.336 --> 00:36:46.671 align:middle line:84%
>> That -- ironically,
that report came

00:36:46.671 --> 00:36:49.307 align:middle line:84%
out on the same day the 911
Commission Report came out.

00:36:49.307 --> 00:36:51.976 align:middle line:84%
Whoever planned that
should lose their job...

00:36:51.976 --> 00:36:52.911 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:36:52.911 --> 00:36:53.778 align:middle line:84%
>> ...because as
Bartlett put it...

00:36:53.778 --> 00:36:55.546 align:middle line:90%
>> It got buried, it got buried.

00:36:55.546 --> 00:36:56.814 align:middle line:84%
>> He said, "We were
looking backwards

00:36:56.814 --> 00:36:58.516 align:middle line:90%
at how the last war started..."

00:36:58.516 --> 00:36:59.851 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:36:59.851 --> 00:37:01.552 align:middle line:84%
>> ..."when this report is
telling us how the next war will

00:37:01.552 --> 00:37:03.121 align:middle line:90%
destroy us completely."

00:37:03.121 --> 00:37:04.689 align:middle line:84%
And nobody was paying
attention to it.

00:37:04.689 --> 00:37:06.991 align:middle line:84%
They were all at the other
end of the building."

00:37:06.991 --> 00:37:09.360 align:middle line:84%
That's what inspired me
to start writing the book.

00:37:09.360 --> 00:37:12.463 align:middle line:84%
Plus I had an incredible
publisher with Tom Doherty

00:37:12.463 --> 00:37:13.765 align:middle line:90%
and Bob Gleason who you know.

00:37:13.765 --> 00:37:15.133 align:middle line:90%
>> My buddies, yeah.

00:37:15.133 --> 00:37:19.837 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah. And Saint Martin's
did a superb job on it and --

00:37:19.837 --> 00:37:23.608 align:middle line:90%
it took four years, actually.

00:37:23.608 --> 00:37:26.678 align:middle line:84%
>> What concerns you the most: a
solar event or a nuke, or both?

00:37:26.678 --> 00:37:28.913 align:middle line:90%
I'll give you that out.

00:37:28.913 --> 00:37:32.750 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, if it happened
would I know the difference?

00:37:32.750 --> 00:37:35.253 align:middle line:90%
>> No. No.

00:37:35.253 --> 00:37:37.789 align:middle line:84%
Once the grid goes,
the grid goes.

00:37:37.789 --> 00:37:39.791 align:middle line:84%
You know, and people are
concerned about, "Oh, my god.

00:37:39.791 --> 00:37:40.925 align:middle line:90%
My power's not on."

00:37:40.925 --> 00:37:41.459 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:37:41.459 --> 00:37:42.827 align:middle line:90%
>> You know.

00:37:42.827 --> 00:37:45.029 align:middle line:84%
And what do you do if it's the
dead of winter and something

00:37:45.029 --> 00:37:47.298 align:middle line:84%
like that happens
when it's 10 degrees

00:37:47.298 --> 00:37:50.802 align:middle line:84%
out on the East Coast
and you have no heat?

00:37:50.802 --> 00:37:52.503 align:middle line:90%
You have no heat source.

00:37:52.503 --> 00:37:55.506 align:middle line:84%
And I guess that's where
that number, that 90% number,

00:37:55.506 --> 00:37:59.410 align:middle line:84%
starts and it grows and I guess
it will be the elderly first

00:37:59.410 --> 00:38:00.111 align:middle line:90%
that go?

00:38:00.111 --> 00:38:00.678 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:38:00.678 --> 00:38:01.612 align:middle line:90%
>> Little kids?

00:38:01.612 --> 00:38:02.447 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:38:02.447 --> 00:38:03.681 align:middle line:90%
>> And then what happens to...

00:38:03.681 --> 00:38:05.216 align:middle line:84%
>> The nursing homes
-- we have millions

00:38:05.216 --> 00:38:06.484 align:middle line:90%
of folks in nursing homes.

00:38:06.484 --> 00:38:08.353 align:middle line:84%
I was very aware of that
because of both of my parents.

00:38:08.353 --> 00:38:09.587 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:38:09.587 --> 00:38:12.557 align:middle line:84%
>> That's -- they're not
designed for anything other

00:38:12.557 --> 00:38:16.160 align:middle line:84%
than a climate control
provided by electricity.

00:38:16.160 --> 00:38:20.631 align:middle line:84%
So we know the horror stories of
what happened in nursing homes

00:38:20.631 --> 00:38:23.334 align:middle line:84%
with Katrina, where
people were found floating

00:38:23.334 --> 00:38:24.435 align:middle line:90%
against the ceiling -- dead.

00:38:24.435 --> 00:38:26.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, yeah.

00:38:26.270 --> 00:38:30.475 align:middle line:84%
>> And if that same kind of
event happened in Chicago

00:38:30.475 --> 00:38:32.877 align:middle line:84%
in January, how many
would be found frozen

00:38:32.877 --> 00:38:33.711 align:middle line:90%
to death a day later?

00:38:33.711 --> 00:38:34.245 align:middle line:90%
>> Many.

00:38:34.245 --> 00:38:34.779 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:38:34.779 --> 00:38:36.114 align:middle line:90%
>> Millions.

00:38:36.114 --> 00:38:39.117 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, George, the last
catastrophe of this scale

00:38:39.117 --> 00:38:40.985 align:middle line:84%
of loss, even remotely
like this,

00:38:40.985 --> 00:38:43.788 align:middle line:84%
was the American Civil
War 150 years ago.

00:38:43.788 --> 00:38:49.660 align:middle line:84%
We, as Americans, do not know
just how intense the suffering

00:38:49.660 --> 00:38:53.031 align:middle line:84%
can be triggered by a
war or a catastrophe.

00:38:53.031 --> 00:38:56.734 align:middle line:84%
I was in Russia some years ago
where I walked across a field

00:38:56.734 --> 00:38:59.670 align:middle line:84%
that was still carpeted
with human bones...

00:38:59.670 --> 00:39:00.772 align:middle line:90%
>> Ach.

00:39:00.772 --> 00:39:03.474 align:middle line:90%
>> ...from a Stalinist massacre.

00:39:03.474 --> 00:39:05.209 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah. You can just feel that.

00:39:05.209 --> 00:39:08.079 align:middle line:84%
>> I could feel them
crunching under my feet

00:39:08.079 --> 00:39:10.581 align:middle line:84%
and it was horrifying
to see the --

00:39:10.581 --> 00:39:13.017 align:middle line:84%
and to see a child's
doll lying there.

00:39:13.017 --> 00:39:15.620 align:middle line:90%
Been out there for 65 years.

00:39:15.620 --> 00:39:17.088 align:middle line:90%
We as Americans are blessed.

00:39:17.088 --> 00:39:19.590 align:middle line:84%
We live in the greatest,
safest place in the world.

00:39:19.590 --> 00:39:20.391 align:middle line:90%
>> So far.

00:39:20.391 --> 00:39:21.726 align:middle line:90%
>> So far.

00:39:21.726 --> 00:39:24.395 align:middle line:84%
But the number's going to
come up sooner or later.

00:39:24.395 --> 00:39:26.063 align:middle line:90%
We got to be ready for it.

00:39:26.063 --> 00:39:28.433 align:middle line:84%
>> Let's take some more
questions for William Forstchen.

00:39:28.433 --> 00:39:32.236 align:middle line:90%
This is a very real possibility.

00:39:32.236 --> 00:39:34.872 align:middle line:90%
I know its a little melancholy.

00:39:34.872 --> 00:39:36.307 align:middle line:90%
Yes sir.

00:39:36.307 --> 00:39:39.710 align:middle line:84%
>> William, thank you
for taking my questions.

00:39:39.710 --> 00:39:42.280 align:middle line:84%
You're, you know,
clearly an expert on this,

00:39:42.280 --> 00:39:45.116 align:middle line:84%
letting people know
what could happen.

00:39:45.116 --> 00:39:49.921 align:middle line:84%
I'm a regular person, you know,
live in the greater Denver area.

00:39:49.921 --> 00:39:51.722 align:middle line:90%
Don't own any firearms.

00:39:51.722 --> 00:39:55.760 align:middle line:84%
So do you have some kind of
like a prepping scenario planned

00:39:55.760 --> 00:39:59.063 align:middle line:84%
out for maybe you, or your
loved ones, or families,

00:39:59.063 --> 00:40:01.032 align:middle line:90%
or what would you suggest?

00:40:01.032 --> 00:40:03.301 align:middle line:84%
You know, I myself
am not a prepper,

00:40:03.301 --> 00:40:05.069 align:middle line:90%
but I know people that are.

00:40:05.069 --> 00:40:07.805 align:middle line:84%
So if something like if a
catastrophe like this were

00:40:07.805 --> 00:40:09.974 align:middle line:90%
to happen, how would --

00:40:09.974 --> 00:40:12.643 align:middle line:84%
what would the first thing
that maybe you would be doing?

00:40:12.643 --> 00:40:13.845 align:middle line:84%
>> So, thank you
for that question

00:40:13.845 --> 00:40:16.214 align:middle line:84%
because I want to
clarify something.

00:40:16.214 --> 00:40:20.251 align:middle line:84%
Too often in public
media it gets

00:40:20.251 --> 00:40:22.954 align:middle line:90%
into this survivalist mentality.

00:40:22.954 --> 00:40:25.556 align:middle line:84%
Now I don't like
survivalists all that much

00:40:25.556 --> 00:40:27.725 align:middle line:84%
because the survivalist
mentality is,

00:40:27.725 --> 00:40:29.360 align:middle line:90%
"I've got mine, George.

00:40:29.360 --> 00:40:30.461 align:middle line:90%
You come to my door.

00:40:30.461 --> 00:40:31.529 align:middle line:90%
The heck with you.

00:40:31.529 --> 00:40:32.563 align:middle line:84%
You're not -- I'm not
going to help you.

00:40:32.563 --> 00:40:33.931 align:middle line:90%
Get away from me."

00:40:33.931 --> 00:40:35.967 align:middle line:84%
>> And you had a chance, George,
when you didn't do anything.

00:40:35.967 --> 00:40:38.369 align:middle line:84%
>> You didn't do
it, so there, there.

00:40:38.369 --> 00:40:40.872 align:middle line:84%
The prepper movement which
has emerged in the last three

00:40:40.872 --> 00:40:45.676 align:middle line:84%
to four years is far more
about us working together.

00:40:45.676 --> 00:40:48.813 align:middle line:84%
How do I get to my
neighbors to work with?

00:40:48.813 --> 00:40:51.949 align:middle line:84%
The doctor down the street
-- let's talk about a plan.

00:40:51.949 --> 00:40:55.453 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't cost all that
much to get started in terms

00:40:55.453 --> 00:40:58.523 align:middle line:84%
of just getting some extra food
and you can get a 50 pound bag

00:40:58.523 --> 00:41:02.660 align:middle line:84%
of rice at one of the
box stores, like $15.

00:41:02.660 --> 00:41:04.896 align:middle line:84%
And then, if you're my neighbor,
George, I'll sit down with you.

00:41:04.896 --> 00:41:07.565 align:middle line:84%
I'll say, George, I'm
not some missionary

00:41:07.565 --> 00:41:09.333 align:middle line:84%
at your doorstep
waving a pamphlet,

00:41:09.333 --> 00:41:11.102 align:middle line:84%
but why don't you read
a couple of these books?

00:41:11.102 --> 00:41:11.936 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:41:11.936 --> 00:41:15.206 align:middle line:90%
>> And then let's talk about it.

00:41:15.206 --> 00:41:18.209 align:middle line:84%
I will not mention the network
but I have a problem with a show

00:41:18.209 --> 00:41:20.511 align:middle line:90%
that deals with preppers.

00:41:20.511 --> 00:41:21.746 align:middle line:90%
It makes them all look

00:41:21.746 --> 00:41:24.048 align:middle line:84%
like they're wearing tinfoil
hats and they're crazy.

00:41:24.048 --> 00:41:27.718 align:middle line:84%
Every prepper I know is
an ordinary person just

00:41:27.718 --> 00:41:28.853 align:middle line:90%
like you, sir.

00:41:28.853 --> 00:41:30.021 align:middle line:84%
And I'm just an ordinary
guy who had [inaudible].

00:41:30.021 --> 00:41:32.056 align:middle line:84%
>> Very serious about
what they doing.

00:41:32.056 --> 00:41:35.760 align:middle line:84%
>> But they are very
oriented towards how do we --

00:41:35.760 --> 00:41:38.629 align:middle line:84%
hey, try and survive
on your own or try

00:41:38.629 --> 00:41:39.931 align:middle line:90%
and survive as a community.

00:41:39.931 --> 00:41:42.767 align:middle line:84%
Survive as a community
is a lot easier.

00:41:42.767 --> 00:41:46.070 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to discuss
personal defense and things

00:41:46.070 --> 00:41:48.306 align:middle line:84%
like that -- it's a
very sensitive issue --

00:41:48.306 --> 00:41:51.375 align:middle line:84%
other than to say if you
make that kind of decision,

00:41:51.375 --> 00:41:55.913 align:middle line:84%
for heaven's sake, follow the
law, get the proper training.

00:41:55.913 --> 00:41:57.281 align:middle line:84%
That's all I'm going
to say on that.

00:41:57.281 --> 00:41:59.951 align:middle line:84%
>> Let's take another video
question for William Forstchen.

00:41:59.951 --> 00:42:02.453 align:middle line:84%
Let's flip the switch,
and here we go.

00:42:02.453 --> 00:42:03.521 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi, William.

00:42:03.521 --> 00:42:04.221 align:middle line:90%
I'm JoAnne.

00:42:04.221 --> 00:42:06.857 align:middle line:90%
I live in Los Angeles.

00:42:06.857 --> 00:42:08.559 align:middle line:84%
How real is the threat
of a solar flare,

00:42:08.559 --> 00:42:11.529 align:middle line:84%
and how long will
we be without power?

00:42:11.529 --> 00:42:12.797 align:middle line:90%
>> Ho, ho, ho, ho.

00:42:12.797 --> 00:42:14.031 align:middle line:90%
Well?

00:42:14.031 --> 00:42:19.036 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, Los Angeles,
JoAnne -- it's real.

00:42:19.036 --> 00:42:20.104 align:middle line:90%
>> And a long time.

00:42:20.104 --> 00:42:24.475 align:middle line:84%
>> It is a very real
long term scenario.

00:42:24.475 --> 00:42:28.546 align:middle line:84%
But even folks in L.A.
can properly prepare.

00:42:28.546 --> 00:42:29.981 align:middle line:84%
In spite of what
we're being told,

00:42:29.981 --> 00:42:31.315 align:middle line:90%
there's an optical illusion...

00:42:31.315 --> 00:42:32.717 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:42:32.717 --> 00:42:34.685 align:middle line:84%
>> ...a missile having taken off
the coast a couple of years ago.

00:42:34.685 --> 00:42:36.821 align:middle line:90%
>> I remember that, story.

00:42:36.821 --> 00:42:38.155 align:middle line:84%
>> Being a prepper
doesn't mean --

00:42:38.155 --> 00:42:40.424 align:middle line:84%
and JoAnne can link
us back into the --

00:42:40.424 --> 00:42:41.659 align:middle line:90%
this gentleman's question.

00:42:41.659 --> 00:42:43.928 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't mean that you're
out in the countryside

00:42:43.928 --> 00:42:46.197 align:middle line:84%
and you have a bunker
or you've got 50 acres

00:42:46.197 --> 00:42:48.132 align:middle line:84%
and you're growing
this and that.

00:42:48.132 --> 00:42:51.235 align:middle line:84%
You can be in a high-rise
in L.A. You could be

00:42:51.235 --> 00:42:54.905 align:middle line:84%
out in the farmlands of
Colorado, or up in the Rockies.

00:42:54.905 --> 00:42:57.408 align:middle line:84%
It's about community,
community, community.

00:42:57.408 --> 00:43:00.311 align:middle line:84%
Working together as
a team, studying --

00:43:00.311 --> 00:43:02.980 align:middle line:84%
there's a lot of literature out
there, a lot of good books now

00:43:02.980 --> 00:43:04.415 align:middle line:90%
on how to be prepared.

00:43:04.415 --> 00:43:07.818 align:middle line:84%
My book is simply a cautionary
novel about what happens

00:43:07.818 --> 00:43:09.954 align:middle line:84%
in a small town in
North Carolina.

00:43:09.954 --> 00:43:12.423 align:middle line:84%
There are dozens of
good instruction manuals

00:43:12.423 --> 00:43:14.291 align:middle line:90%
out there now as well, as to how

00:43:14.291 --> 00:43:15.926 align:middle line:84%
to get started, how
to get ready.

00:43:15.926 --> 00:43:18.562 align:middle line:84%
And remember, it's just
not for CME or EMP.

00:43:18.562 --> 00:43:23.501 align:middle line:84%
It could be earthquake, could
be storms, any number of things.

00:43:23.501 --> 00:43:26.203 align:middle line:84%
>> Let's take another question
from the audience for William.

00:43:26.203 --> 00:43:26.904 align:middle line:90%
Who's got one?

00:43:26.904 --> 00:43:28.306 align:middle line:90%
Yes, way in the back.

00:43:28.306 --> 00:43:30.641 align:middle line:84%
>> Thank you for
taking my question.

00:43:30.641 --> 00:43:33.077 align:middle line:84%
William, considering
the devastation

00:43:33.077 --> 00:43:35.613 align:middle line:90%
that an EMP event would cause,

00:43:35.613 --> 00:43:38.849 align:middle line:84%
why wouldn't power
companies be taking steps

00:43:38.849 --> 00:43:41.719 align:middle line:84%
in all ways possible
to protect us --

00:43:41.719 --> 00:43:45.022 align:middle line:84%
protect their infrastructure
and us from such an event?

00:43:45.022 --> 00:43:47.191 align:middle line:90%
>> Ah, well.

00:43:47.191 --> 00:43:47.892 align:middle line:90%
>> Ahhhhhh.

00:43:47.892 --> 00:43:48.693 align:middle line:90%
>> Really good question.

00:43:48.693 --> 00:43:50.161 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm from North Carolina.

00:43:50.161 --> 00:43:54.131 align:middle line:84%
I have yet quite to
master the accent.

00:43:54.131 --> 00:43:55.499 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the Jersey
does come out,

00:43:55.499 --> 00:43:59.437 align:middle line:84%
but there was a big argument
about this in North Carolina

00:43:59.437 --> 00:44:00.905 align:middle line:90%
about a year or two ago,

00:44:00.905 --> 00:44:04.575 align:middle line:84%
in which a commission
there dismissed the threat.

00:44:04.575 --> 00:44:07.878 align:middle line:84%
The bottom line is
the increased cost

00:44:07.878 --> 00:44:09.914 align:middle line:84%
to start preparing
our infrastructure is

00:44:09.914 --> 00:44:13.984 align:middle line:90%
about 10% to 15% increase.

00:44:13.984 --> 00:44:15.553 align:middle line:84%
You've got to replace
an old power line.

00:44:15.553 --> 00:44:17.655 align:middle line:84%
>> Quite, and it's
got to be done.

00:44:17.655 --> 00:44:20.458 align:middle line:84%
>> Ten to 15% more
you can proof it.

00:44:20.458 --> 00:44:22.660 align:middle line:84%
An analogy I give
there is hardening.

00:44:22.660 --> 00:44:24.095 align:middle line:90%
If we just harden parts

00:44:24.095 --> 00:44:26.897 align:middle line:84%
of our infrastructure
it's like a spider web.

00:44:26.897 --> 00:44:28.799 align:middle line:84%
Remember the spider webs,
we'd see in the lawn

00:44:28.799 --> 00:44:30.835 align:middle line:90%
in the morning covered in dew?

00:44:30.835 --> 00:44:32.269 align:middle line:84%
And if you're a bit of
a wacky kid you have

00:44:32.269 --> 00:44:33.804 align:middle line:90%
to put a match under it.

00:44:33.804 --> 00:44:35.706 align:middle line:84%
Well, imagine if that
poor spider's in there.

00:44:35.706 --> 00:44:37.007 align:middle line:90%
Darn kid again.

00:44:37.007 --> 00:44:39.577 align:middle line:84%
But the spider had
hardened only eight or ten

00:44:39.577 --> 00:44:42.079 align:middle line:84%
of those threads
that were fireproof.

00:44:42.079 --> 00:44:45.382 align:middle line:84%
How much easier to spin
the rest of the thread back

00:44:45.382 --> 00:44:49.820 align:middle line:84%
but also provide emergency
linkage along those lines.

00:44:49.820 --> 00:44:53.591 align:middle line:84%
The power companies themselves
do not want to invest.

00:44:53.591 --> 00:44:55.459 align:middle line:84%
>> They want the
government to do it for them.

00:44:55.459 --> 00:44:56.994 align:middle line:90%
>> Right! You got it!

00:44:56.994 --> 00:45:00.164 align:middle line:84%
And there's even a bit of a
cynical -- well, if it happens,

00:45:00.164 --> 00:45:04.168 align:middle line:84%
we're all messed up anyhow,
and our stockbrokers --

00:45:04.168 --> 00:45:05.736 align:middle line:84%
our stockholders
[multiple voices].

00:45:05.736 --> 00:45:07.772 align:middle line:84%
>> The sad part about
it is, William,

00:45:07.772 --> 00:45:08.873 align:middle line:90%
as you will demonstrate...

00:45:08.873 --> 00:45:09.874 align:middle line:90%
>> It's easy.

00:45:09.874 --> 00:45:11.041 align:middle line:90%
>> You can do it.

00:45:11.041 --> 00:45:12.009 align:middle line:90%
You can fix it.

00:45:12.009 --> 00:45:12.777 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:45:12.777 --> 00:45:15.146 align:middle line:90%
>> One more question here.

00:45:15.146 --> 00:45:15.679 align:middle line:90%
Who's got one?

00:45:15.679 --> 00:45:16.680 align:middle line:90%
Yes, sir.

00:45:16.680 --> 00:45:17.681 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you, William.

00:45:17.681 --> 00:45:18.449 align:middle line:90%
Just a question.

00:45:18.449 --> 00:45:19.550 align:middle line:90%
You spoke about hardening.

00:45:19.550 --> 00:45:20.951 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:45:20.951 --> 00:45:23.721 align:middle line:84%
>> Are there any methods that
a person could do practically

00:45:23.721 --> 00:45:27.391 align:middle line:84%
to harden maybe generators
or any kind

00:45:27.391 --> 00:45:31.428 align:middle line:84%
of personal items you might
need for the short term?

00:45:31.428 --> 00:45:34.698 align:middle line:84%
>> It just so happens that
Mr. Noory here insisted

00:45:34.698 --> 00:45:37.935 align:middle line:84%
that I bring something along
to demonstrate that with.

00:45:37.935 --> 00:45:39.270 align:middle line:90%
And, yes.

00:45:39.270 --> 00:45:40.671 align:middle line:90%
>> We'll do that soon.

00:45:40.671 --> 00:45:43.240 align:middle line:84%
>> And the -- again, I recommend
a number of different manuals.

00:45:43.240 --> 00:45:48.112 align:middle line:84%
You can find out there
how to prepare for EMP.

00:45:48.112 --> 00:45:49.413 align:middle line:90%
Have back-up parts.

00:45:49.413 --> 00:45:52.783 align:middle line:84%
In fact, everybody has
what's called a Faraday Cage

00:45:52.783 --> 00:45:54.218 align:middle line:90%
in their house already.

00:45:54.218 --> 00:45:55.719 align:middle line:90%
It's called a microwave oven.

00:45:55.719 --> 00:45:57.521 align:middle line:90%
You take an old microwave oven.

00:45:57.521 --> 00:45:58.956 align:middle line:84%
You can throw some
electronics in it.

00:45:58.956 --> 00:46:04.261 align:middle line:84%
Make sure it's properly
grounded and it will survive.

00:46:04.261 --> 00:46:06.330 align:middle line:84%
Hardening is not
all that difficult.

00:46:06.330 --> 00:46:09.233 align:middle line:84%
Now you might lose you
60-inch television screen,

00:46:09.233 --> 00:46:11.101 align:middle line:84%
but there ain't going to be
any signals coming to that

00:46:11.101 --> 00:46:13.070 align:middle line:90%
for some time to come.

00:46:13.070 --> 00:46:15.506 align:middle line:84%
But everybody should
have in their home,

00:46:15.506 --> 00:46:20.244 align:middle line:84%
in a secure Farraday,
F-A-R-A-D-A-Y.

00:46:20.244 --> 00:46:22.980 align:middle line:84%
You can find instructions
for that on the Internet.

00:46:22.980 --> 00:46:24.849 align:middle line:90%
I have an emergency radio

00:46:24.849 --> 00:46:26.517 align:middle line:84%
that runs off batteries
or hand-crank...

00:46:26.517 --> 00:46:27.484 align:middle line:90%
>> Or solar.

00:46:27.484 --> 00:46:30.154 align:middle line:84%
>> I have it inside
a Faraday bag.

00:46:30.154 --> 00:46:33.324 align:middle line:84%
Great to pull out after an
event, so I'm up and running

00:46:33.324 --> 00:46:36.861 align:middle line:90%
with news, and advice reports.

00:46:36.861 --> 00:46:38.896 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you for that question.

00:46:38.896 --> 00:46:42.132 align:middle line:90%
What are other countries doing?

00:46:42.132 --> 00:46:44.935 align:middle line:84%
Is anybody doing
anything about this?

00:46:44.935 --> 00:46:46.337 align:middle line:90%
>> Ooh. Most of its classified.

00:46:46.337 --> 00:46:47.705 align:middle line:90%
Are they...

00:46:47.705 --> 00:46:49.807 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean they all have the
some possible outcome, right?

00:46:49.807 --> 00:46:50.941 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:46:50.941 --> 00:46:53.577 align:middle line:84%
>> The sun is the sun
and a nuke is a nuke.

00:46:53.577 --> 00:46:55.946 align:middle line:90%
>> I can't answer that.

00:46:55.946 --> 00:46:57.615 align:middle line:90%
And at conferences I have asked

00:46:57.615 --> 00:46:59.183 align:middle line:84%
or I would have --
what is Russia doing?

00:46:59.183 --> 00:47:00.117 align:middle line:90%
What is China doing?

00:47:00.117 --> 00:47:01.185 align:middle line:90%
>> What is China doing?

00:47:01.185 --> 00:47:03.053 align:middle line:84%
>> Switzerland, I
understand, they're --

00:47:03.053 --> 00:47:04.622 align:middle line:84%
well, Switzerland's
always on top of things.

00:47:04.622 --> 00:47:05.322 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:47:05.322 --> 00:47:07.958 align:middle line:90%
>> I don't know.

00:47:07.958 --> 00:47:10.594 align:middle line:90%
And see, there as well, it's --

00:47:11.862 --> 00:47:15.199 align:middle line:84%
I have very little regard
for the U.N., but they --

00:47:15.199 --> 00:47:17.334 align:middle line:84%
if we're dealing with a
global situation like BME...

00:47:17.334 --> 00:47:18.636 align:middle line:90%
>> Which is a global fix.

00:47:18.636 --> 00:47:20.638 align:middle line:84%
>>...it should be a global
fix and we should be talking

00:47:20.638 --> 00:47:23.040 align:middle line:84%
about how do we work
as a global community?

00:47:23.040 --> 00:47:25.175 align:middle line:90%
One, to prepare, but secondly,

00:47:25.175 --> 00:47:27.344 align:middle line:84%
think of the communications
breakdown and the potential

00:47:27.344 --> 00:47:30.414 align:middle line:84%
for global war triggering
within a matter of days

00:47:30.414 --> 00:47:32.182 align:middle line:84%
as people are scrambling
for resources...

00:47:32.182 --> 00:47:33.017 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:47:33.017 --> 00:47:34.251 align:middle line:90%
>> ...or saying, "Wait a minute.

00:47:34.251 --> 00:47:36.854 align:middle line:84%
You did this to us --
we'regoing to watch on you."

00:47:36.854 --> 00:47:37.955 align:middle line:90%
And the confusion...

00:47:37.955 --> 00:47:39.056 align:middle line:90%
>> Total collapse.

00:47:39.056 --> 00:47:39.823 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:47:39.823 --> 00:47:40.624 align:middle line:90%
>> Let's do an experiment.

00:47:40.624 --> 00:47:41.392 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:47:41.392 --> 00:47:43.661 align:middle line:90%
>> What do you want to do?

00:47:43.661 --> 00:47:44.762 align:middle line:90%
>> It just so happens...

00:47:44.762 --> 00:47:47.164 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you told me
to bring my cell phone,

00:47:47.164 --> 00:47:49.099 align:middle line:90%
and you have one, too.

00:47:49.099 --> 00:47:50.200 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:47:50.200 --> 00:47:51.402 align:middle line:84%
>> Can you tell me what
I'm supposed to do?

00:47:51.402 --> 00:47:53.037 align:middle line:90%
>> Okay. Trust us.

00:47:53.037 --> 00:47:55.205 align:middle line:90%
We tested this before.

00:47:55.205 --> 00:47:58.609 align:middle line:84%
If he calls me the
signal will come through.

00:47:58.609 --> 00:48:01.845 align:middle line:90%
This is a Faraday bag.

00:48:01.845 --> 00:48:04.748 align:middle line:84%
You can buy it online or
in any number of stores.

00:48:04.748 --> 00:48:07.885 align:middle line:84%
I think I got this one
for about five bucks.

00:48:07.885 --> 00:48:11.355 align:middle line:84%
You can get them as
big as six feet across.

00:48:11.355 --> 00:48:12.923 align:middle line:90%
Nothing up my sleeve.

00:48:12.923 --> 00:48:15.926 align:middle line:90%
I got my cell phone in.

00:48:15.926 --> 00:48:16.894 align:middle line:90%
Seal it.

00:48:16.894 --> 00:48:19.530 align:middle line:90%
>> And now I'm to dial you up?

00:48:19.530 --> 00:48:20.598 align:middle line:90%
>> Call me.

00:48:20.598 --> 00:48:21.765 align:middle line:90%
>> All right.

00:48:21.765 --> 00:48:22.499 align:middle line:84%
>> If it works, it's
going to be embarrassing.

00:48:22.499 --> 00:48:23.567 align:middle line:90%
>> We will do that.

00:48:23.567 --> 00:48:24.868 align:middle line:90%
Let's see what happens.

00:48:24.868 --> 00:48:26.870 align:middle line:90%
Let me put it on speaker.

00:48:26.870 --> 00:48:29.673 align:middle line:84%
So maybe we'll hear
[phone ringing] me ringing.

00:48:29.673 --> 00:48:30.607 align:middle line:90%
>> Okay [phone ringing].

00:48:30.607 --> 00:48:33.811 align:middle line:90%
My phone's not ringing.

00:48:33.811 --> 00:48:35.045 align:middle line:84%
>> If it's not [phone
ringing]...

00:48:35.045 --> 00:48:35.746 align:middle line:90%
>> Well...

00:48:35.746 --> 00:48:36.814 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, you want to do...

00:48:36.814 --> 00:48:37.281 align:middle line:84%
>> Whoa, I knew it
was going to do that!

00:48:37.281 --> 00:48:37.982 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:48:37.982 --> 00:48:39.083 align:middle line:90%
>> You opened the bag.

00:48:39.083 --> 00:48:39.783 align:middle line:84%
>> So I have to open
the bag [phone ringing].

00:48:39.783 --> 00:48:40.884 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah [phone ringing].

00:48:40.884 --> 00:48:42.519 align:middle line:84%
>> But the moment I
start to open the bag...

00:48:42.519 --> 00:48:43.253 align:middle line:90%
>> There it is.

00:48:43.253 --> 00:48:46.123 align:middle line:90%
>> ...it came back on.

00:48:46.123 --> 00:48:47.958 align:middle line:90%
That's $5.

00:48:47.958 --> 00:48:49.693 align:middle line:84%
>> And what would
you do with this?

00:48:49.693 --> 00:48:51.261 align:middle line:90%
>> What would I do with that?

00:48:51.261 --> 00:48:54.765 align:middle line:84%
Well, I could put my head
in it if it was big enough,

00:48:54.765 --> 00:48:58.535 align:middle line:84%
but this is a perfect thing for
what the one gentleman asked

00:48:58.535 --> 00:49:00.604 align:middle line:90%
about -- precious electronics.

00:49:00.604 --> 00:49:01.805 align:middle line:90%
>> His ham radio?

00:49:01.805 --> 00:49:03.273 align:middle line:90%
>> Ham radio.

00:49:03.273 --> 00:49:07.611 align:middle line:84%
Oh, ham radios -- all ham radio
operators know, definitely --

00:49:07.611 --> 00:49:09.480 align:middle line:84%
don't have your antenna
hooked up all the time

00:49:09.480 --> 00:49:11.181 align:middle line:84%
because that will
feed a signal in.

00:49:11.181 --> 00:49:12.149 align:middle line:90%
>> Okay.

00:49:12.149 --> 00:49:13.617 align:middle line:84%
>> But if I had ham
radio equipment,

00:49:13.617 --> 00:49:15.686 align:middle line:84%
I'd get one of those
six by six bags.

00:49:15.686 --> 00:49:18.288 align:middle line:84%
They don't cost that
much relatively speaking.

00:49:18.288 --> 00:49:20.290 align:middle line:90%
Stuff it all in there.

00:49:20.290 --> 00:49:23.927 align:middle line:84%
This can protect you from
all of your electronics,

00:49:23.927 --> 00:49:26.797 align:middle line:90%
from a major CME/EMP event.

00:49:26.797 --> 00:49:30.034 align:middle line:84%
And then when you know it's
safe to open them back up,

00:49:30.034 --> 00:49:32.503 align:middle line:84%
you pull them out and
you have your systems

00:49:32.503 --> 00:49:33.604 align:middle line:90%
up and running again.

00:49:33.604 --> 00:49:34.371 align:middle line:90%
>> All right.

00:49:34.371 --> 00:49:35.939 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about the grid.

00:49:35.939 --> 00:49:40.010 align:middle line:84%
How do you insulate the
grid from a pulse attack

00:49:40.010 --> 00:49:42.212 align:middle line:90%
or a coronal mass ejection?

00:49:42.212 --> 00:49:43.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Let's do the analogy again

00:49:43.380 --> 00:49:45.916 align:middle line:84%
of here's the generator,
there's your house.

00:49:45.916 --> 00:49:47.184 align:middle line:90%
>> All right.

00:49:47.184 --> 00:49:50.754 align:middle line:84%
>> That's a long
wire, all right?

00:49:50.754 --> 00:49:54.124 align:middle line:84%
And if we took that wire
and put it all together,

00:49:54.124 --> 00:49:55.759 align:middle line:84%
that's quite a few
square meters...

00:49:55.759 --> 00:49:56.326 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm-mm.

00:49:56.326 --> 00:49:57.661 align:middle line:90%
>> ...of wire.

00:49:57.661 --> 00:50:01.732 align:middle line:84%
When you have a discharge
coming down and the thousands

00:50:01.732 --> 00:50:02.933 align:middle line:90%
of volts per square meter --

00:50:02.933 --> 00:50:05.269 align:middle line:84%
we've all stood underneath
high tension lines.

00:50:05.269 --> 00:50:07.237 align:middle line:84%
You could actually
hear them popping.

00:50:07.237 --> 00:50:08.605 align:middle line:90%
>> You can hear the buzz.

00:50:08.605 --> 00:50:10.774 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, imagine if somebody
get a million more volts popped

00:50:10.774 --> 00:50:12.342 align:middle line:90%
out to them.

00:50:12.342 --> 00:50:13.977 align:middle line:90%
You're gone, all right?

00:50:13.977 --> 00:50:21.952 align:middle line:84%
But suppose we put breakers
at very regular intervals.

00:50:21.952 --> 00:50:24.054 align:middle line:84%
>> So the whole thing
doesn't get it you mean.

00:50:24.054 --> 00:50:27.257 align:middle line:84%
>> And also, the
breakers you got now --

00:50:27.257 --> 00:50:32.129 align:middle line:84%
does it not seem that when
you buy that new hi-def wi TV,

00:50:32.129 --> 00:50:34.364 align:middle line:84%
that the next day a lightning
bolt hits next to your house?

00:50:34.364 --> 00:50:35.766 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:50:35.766 --> 00:50:38.335 align:middle line:84%
>> And you go, darn, I should
have gotten the surge arrester.

00:50:38.335 --> 00:50:42.106 align:middle line:84%
Current surge arresters
are not good enough...

00:50:42.106 --> 00:50:43.073 align:middle line:90%
>> For one of these.

00:50:43.073 --> 00:50:44.475 align:middle line:90%
>> ...for one of these.

00:50:44.475 --> 00:50:46.877 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we've got to get into
some technical stuff, but the...

00:50:46.877 --> 00:50:48.312 align:middle line:84%
>> But is it doable
[multiple voices]?

00:50:48.312 --> 00:50:49.646 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes, it is.

00:50:49.646 --> 00:50:51.448 align:middle line:90%
You can make surge protectors.

